title: vegetable casserole
directions: Butter bottom and sides of casserole dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese; blend well.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and slightly browned.
Serves 10.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Grease baking dish.
Combine vegetables, onion, pepper and cheese in dish.
Combine milk, Bisquick and eggs.
Stir together. Pats of butter on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: mom's gazpacho
directions: Rub large bowl with garlic.
Empty taco seasoning into bowl. Add tomato juice and stir.
Peel tomatoes, remove cores and chop into small pieces.
Add tomatoes, cucumbers, green pepper and onion to tomato juice. Then add olive oil, vinegar and cilantro; mix well. Chill before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Stir in flour.
Chill.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Shape into shells.

title: pat's potato soup
directions: Add potatoes, onions and water in a large pot.
Bring to boil. Add salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Mash in pot. Add butter and milk and cook until flavor mixes and butter melts.
Serve hot with crackers or corn bread.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a shallow baking sheet. The pan should hold all the food in a single layer, with a little space between.
Wash and cut potatoes in 3-inch chunks.
Place carrots and potatoes on baking pan and sprinkle with a little oil. Toss to coat.
Add pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and about 1 teaspoon thyme.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook all ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Put into pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Beat egg white and put on pie.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine hamburger and sausage in skillet and cook until done. In separate bowl, combine cooked hamburger, sausage, Velveeta and salsa.
Mix well until cheese melts.
Serve hot with your favorite chip.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until just tender but firm (do not overcook).
Let cool.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package. Drain any water. In separate bowl, mix together all other ingredients. Then add the broccoli. Put in an 8 x 8 dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot and sour shrimp
directions: Combine shrimp, 2 tablespoons sherry and ginger in bowl. Marinate 30 minutes.
Mix remaining sherry, chicken broth, soy sauce, catsup, cornstarch, vinegar, sugar, sesame oil and cayenne pepper in small bowl.
Heat 2 teaspoons oil in wok or heavy skillet over high heat.
Add walnuts; stir-fry 1 minute and transfer to plate, using slotted spoon.
Add watercress and stir-fry until wilted, about 1 minute.
Divide among plates.
Add 2 teaspoons oil, peppers and garlic to wok and stir-fry 1 minute. Add remaining 2 teaspoons oil, shrimp mixture and onions. Stir-fry 1 minute or until shrimp is pink.
Stir in stock mixture; cook until sauce is thick and clear, stirring frequently, about 2 minutes.
Spoon sauce and shrimp over watercress.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes 4 servings, about 256 calories per serving.

title: chicken livers hong kong
directions: Cut chicken liver in half.
Place in a medium bowl. Refrigerate 1 hour, covered.
Skewer a piece of liver and water chestnut on wooden picks.
Place on broiler rack, broil under preheated hot broiler until cooked as desired, about 2 minutes on each side.
About 58 calories per serving.

title: oatmeal or lace cookies
directions: Cream butter and light brown sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put foil on cookie sheet and spray with nonstick spray.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and salt. Add eggs, bananas and soda. Dissolve in hot water. Add flour and nuts (if desired). Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add sour cream.
Mix flour, soda and salt together; add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in extract.
Turn batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Test and bake longer if needed.
(If desired, a lemon glaze may be used.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease some cookie sheets.
Cream the butter and peanut butter together.
Beat in the sugars, then add the egg and vanilla and mix well.
Mix together the baking soda and flour and add to the first mixture, combining thoroughly.
Arrange by teaspoonfuls on the cookie sheets about 1 1/2 inches apart. Press each one flat with the back of a floured spoon.
Bake about 7 minutes until firm.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium.
Add rice and brown, stirring constantly.
When brown, add onions and saute until soft.
Add tomato sauce, spices and fry for about 5 seconds.
Add 1 cup chicken broth and 1/2 cup water and meat.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer until rice is cooked, about 15 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Dredge in flour and brown in a little butter.
Place in heavy skillet or electric frying pan. Sprinkle with garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour over enough hot water to prevent sticking while cooking, about 1 cup.
Cook 2 hours over low heat.
Add mushrooms, liquid, onions, green pepper and ketchup.
Cook 1 hour.
Last 1/2 hour, leave off lid of pan to let juice thicken.
You may have to take out meat at end and boil down the liquid to make a thickened gravy.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and 1 stick margarine in microwave in glass 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper in another bowl.
Stir and combine well with hash browns. Top with crushed cornflakes mixed with 1 stick melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour until bubbly.
Let sit for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: Combine the cake mix with evaporated milk and butter.
Press half of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Melt the caramels with the other 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Cool slightly.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips over top of caramels.
Top with remaining cake mix.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on a cookie sheet biscuit size.
Bake at 400°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain grease.
Add egg, 1 can of soup, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Stir and put in casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Spread on casserole.
Combine other can of soup and cheese; spread on top of potatoes.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: homemade irish creme
directions: Blend first four ingredients with an electric mixer or blender.
Stir in whiskey.
Pour into bottles and keep refrigerated.
Shake gently before each use.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread completely and roll out in a circle 1/4 inch thick. Brown sausage (crumbled) with chopped onion and chopped pepper. Add Italian seasoning; drain.
Return to heat and add Mozzarella cheese until stringy.
Spread sausage mixture in the middle of the bread and roll.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with sesame seed, if desired.
Let rise for approximately 30 minutes and bake at 350° until bread is golden brown.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Add peanut butter.
Blend. Pour over Chex.
Stir gently until coated.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; beat for 5 minutes. Layer bananas, wafers and pudding.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix. Put on crust.

title: artichoke dip(serves 8)
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
If smooth consistency is desired, a food processor or blender may be used.
Pour into an ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with Fritos or Melba toast rounds.

title: arkansas brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday leg of lamb(french style)
directions: Let leg of lamb reach room temperature.
Pierce to bone with narrow knife every 2-inches and insert small whole or large half cloves of fresh peeled garlic.
Liberally cover all sides with garlic salt, then fresh rosemary leaves.
Preheat oven to 450°. Place lamb on a roasting pan and cook for 40 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Do not open oven door for 3 hours.
Lamb will be juicy and tender, medium rare.
Serve with French mustard.

title: sour cream potato soup *
directions: Cover potatoes, carrot and onion with 4 cups water.
Add salt and boil about 40 minutes, covered.
Thicken with flour.
Add sour cream and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.
This cannot be frozen.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Saute pepper and onion in butter until soft. Add tomatoes to pepper and onion mixture. Add crawfish tails and simmer for 10 minutes. Add cooked rice.
Put mixture in buttered casserole dish. Top with slices of cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery seed, celery, onion, salt and pepper. Dice eggs and add to potato mixture. Add remaining ingredients. Chill several hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well, adding melted butter last.
Mix and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Roll batter into balls, about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cold, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: grasshopper pie(yields 1 pie)
directions: Soften ice cream at room temperature for 10 minutes or until you can spoon spread in pie crust.
Score top with fork and pour 1/4 cup of chocolate syrup over top.
Freeze overnight.
Beat heavy cream with the 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Pile on top.
Drizzle remaining 2 teaspoons chocolate syrup and 2 teaspoons creme de menthe on top.
Enjoy!

title: pretzel salad
directions: Break pretzels and place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and sugar.
Pour over pretzels.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°. Let cool.
Break with knife.
Mix cheese, sugar, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Mix jello and hot water.
Add strawberries.
Allow to gel slightly.
Pour over cheese mixture.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, oil, pineapple and vanilla until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time; stir in sweet potatoes and pecans.
Pour into 13-inch pan or angel food pan, which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Beat together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: lush
directions: FIRST LAYER: Mix flour, walnuts and softened butter. Press into bottom of 9 x 14 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown and cool.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Fold all together and enjoy!
Very rich.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind pepper and onion.
Mix pepper, onion, sugar and vinegar and bring to a rolling boil for about 3 minutes.
Set off stove; let set 5 minutes.
Add Certo, stirring occasionally; pour in jars and seal.
Very good on vegetables; also, with crackers as a snack.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit pops
directions: Mix juice and sweetened condensed milk in bowl using wire whisk.
Carefully pour some of mixture into measuring cup with a pouring spout.
Put paper cups into square pan.
Fill paper cups almost to the top.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Remove from freezer and put wooden sticks in center on each "pop."
Return to freezer for 5 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll tortillas up and slice crosswise.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crab and shrimp au gratin
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper with 1 cup milk.
Beat all lumps out.
Add Cheez Whiz to other cup of milk in double boiler.
When Cheez Whiz is melted, add flour mixture and Tabasco.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Add shrimp and crab meat.
Pour into a casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine dates, nuts, soda, salt and butter with 2 cups boiling water.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, then flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for little loaves or 1 hour and 15 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: In bowl place cream cheese.
Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Cover.
Chill several hours.
Serve with Pepperidge Farms Butter Thins.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine and serve over crushed ice. Serves 40 to 50.

title: baked fruit
directions: Cook the sauce until smooth and pour over the fruit. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: no bake apricot cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: caramel corn oven baked
directions: Boil brown sugar, corn syrup, oleo and cream of tartar for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add syrup to popped corn and mix well.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix together and press into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Mix together and spread cucumber mixture on white bread. Chill or freeze before trimming edges of bread. Cut into six bite-sized sandwiches. Freezing prepared sandwiches for a couple of days before using is o.k.
Be sure to drain liquid from shredded cucumbers as this might cause cucumbers to turn dark when chilled or frozen.

title: tortilla snack
directions: Mix together green chilies and cream cheese until smooth. Spread thin layer of mixture on tortilla.
Roll up.
Chill for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Cut into bite size portions.
Dip into picante sauce.

title: cholesterol free corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, sweetener, salt and margarine in bowl. Add hot water and stir until all is mixed together.
Mix the baking powder with 1/4 cup of skim milk and add to mixture.
Add Egg Beaters and rest of milk.
Bake in pan approximately 8 x 11-inch for 1 hour at 350°.

title: candied fruit for fruit cakes
directions: Collect fruit peel in freezer until you have 4 each of orange, lemon, and grapefruit. Wash and dice peelings very small. Slowly boil sugar, water and corn syrup over low heat for 30 minutes. Add peels and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour (it is done when all syrup has been absorbed). Sprinkle some sugar on wax paper; lay peels on it and toss to distribute. Let set for a couple of days to dry out. Will last indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: cajun country hot apple drink
directions: Mix together and heat until candy melts.

title: prize-winning meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press firmly into ungreased pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix and bake 10-12 minutes.

title: crusty baked chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour butter in a shallow baking dish.
Dip chicken in chip mixture, then in egg mixture and back in chip mixture.
Place pieces side by side in dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's favorite banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Add eggs and mix.
Mix in banana.
Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl. Then gradually add to banana mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning according to directions on package.
Cook rice according to the package.
Melt Velveeta and add tomatoes.
Pour Velveeta and tomatoes and rice into ground beef.
Mix well and pour into 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with tortilla chips (crushed).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Makes enough for 5 chickens.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put on low and cook over night or around 8 hours.
Add 4 packages of brown gravy mix and stir.
Cook on low for 30 minutes then turn on warm.
Serve with homemade bread and salad.

title: mexican strata
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chips and cheese; combine all other ingredients and pour over chips and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: light bread fruit pie
directions: Spread the filling in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Trim crusts from the bread and lay on top of the pie filling.
Melt the butter or margarine.
Mix with the sugar, flour and egg.
Pour over the bread.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven.
Remove from heat; add Worcestershire sauce, catsup and hot sauce, stirring well.
Add pecans, stirring to coat.
Spread pecans evenly in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Place pecans on paper towels; sprinkle lightly with salt and cool completely.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: chile con carne
directions: Chop up onion and celery and add to ground beef in large skillet or large heavy saucepan.
Brown the beef first, then add the onions and celery.
Let onions and celery get soft, then add tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 cup water, kidney beans, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stir until well mixed.
Add bay leaf.
Turn heat to simmer.
Cook 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Serves 4.

title: tom's hot chocolate
directions: Mix ingredients together.
To get "bombed" replace the vanilla extract with 2 drops of spearmint extract.

title: corn casserole
directions: In oblong baking dish melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Set aside. Mix both cans of corn, Jiffy cornmeal and sour cream.
Pour into dish with melted margarine.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 325°.
Top with cheese (optional) and bake until it melts.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese coarse.
Chop 3 teaspoons of parsley. In a 3-quart saucepan, bring 1 cup of water to boil.
Add cauliflower, separating with a fork.
Cook until tender, but don't drain the water.
Save 1 cup of cauliflower florets for garnish. Put celery soup in medium bowl.
Beat with wire whisk while slowly adding milk.
Make sure there are no lumps.
Add celery soup and milk mixture to cauliflower and cooking water left in saucepan. Add grated cheese; mix well. Cook over moderately high heat, stirring frequently until mixture begins to boil.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake(makes 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch or three 8-inch round cake pans.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir together flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with vanilla and milk, beating at low speed, until well combined.
Do not overbeat.
Turn into prepared pans and bake until golden and centers spring back when gently pressed, about 30 to 35 minutes for 9-inch pans or 25 to 30 minutes for 8-inch pans. Cool 5 minutes in pans.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: short cut lasagna
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce mix and V-8 juice.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Cover bottom oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch (3-quart) casserole dish with thin layer meat sauce.
Then add layer each uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cotillion punch
directions: Freeze in small round plastic containers.
It will not freeze hard.
Take out about 30 minutes in advance so it will slip out of container easily.
Pour ginger ale over frozen punch and stir.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Arrange corned beef over sauerkraut mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Remove crust from bread to make 2 1/2-inch squares.
Halve each square diagonally into triangles; arrange bread over cheese completely covering top of casserole. Brush with melted butter.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground meat. Add onions. Stir in taco mix until meat is coated well.
In crock-pot, add water, tomatoes and beans. Add meat and simmer for approximately 3 to 4 hours. Spoon over chips. Top with sour cream and grated cheese (sprinkle jalapenos too if desired).
Serves 4.

title: bible school sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll into balls about the size of a quarter and place on greased cookie sheet.
Mash down with fingertips.
Press down with glass where bottom has been dipped in water (for first cookie only).
Then dip in white sugar for each cookie.
Bake at 375° only until lightly brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Batter will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken 1/2 hour at 350°, then add Mozzarella cheese on top and spaghetti sauce, and continue to cook for 1/2 hour more.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done (may take up to 60 minutes).

title: peanut butter spread
directions: Let juice stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
In bowl, mix peanut butter and sour cream.
Stir in juice until smooth. Serve with fruit or toast.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: "roast" makes own gravy
directions: In bottom of roasting pan (can line with tinfoil if you wish), spread can of celery or mushroom soup (I use 2 cans of each, sometimes more).
It depends on how much gravy you want.
Slice one onion on top of soup that was spread on bottom of pan.
Add 1 can of mushrooms (or whatever amount you want).
Season meat (not too heavy) and place on top of soup.

title: rizogalo (rice pudding)
directions: Simmer rice in water and milk for about 45 minutes or until sauce is thick and rice is soft.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and vanilla together until thick and creamy.
Gradually stir hot rice mixture into eggs and return to saucepan.
Add salt and cook over low heat for several minutes, stirring constantly to prevent curdling.
Ladle into pudding dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon. Cool.
Place in refrigerator and serve cold.

title: cheerios nuttyos
directions: Brush jelly roll pan with oleo.
Heat brown sugar, syrup, butter and salt in large saucepan on medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and nuts until well coated.

title: cheesed zucchini
directions: Peel and quarter the zucchini.
Cover bottom of shallow baking dish with zucchini.
Sprinkle with salt, garlic salt, oregano and pepper.
Slice the tomatoes; place over squash.
Season same as for squash.
Slice enough onion to make a layer; season as before. Over onion, layer sharp cheese slices.
Top with layer of bacon strips.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Whisk together in a small bowl.
Chill until ready to serve. Great for luncheon fruit salad.

title: chocolate, mascarpone and fruit shortcakes
directions: Chill a medium mixing bowl and the beaters of an electric mixer in the refrigerator while preparing the shortcakes.

title: turkey hash
directions: Heat oil in saucepan on medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Combine potatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat mixture thoroughly (about 5 minutes).
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot walnut muffins
directions: Sift together first six ingredients.
Toss walnuts into dry mixture.
Cut
in
butter; add milk, egg and carrots.
Mix lightly, being
careful
not
to
overmix.	Spoon into greased muffin tins until almost full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 20 minutes.
Makes one dozen muffins.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, vinegar and milk 4 minutes.
After it starts boiling, add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and nuts. Mix well and dump into greased pan.
Cool.

title: flank steak teriyaki barbecue
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add steak.
Marinate at least 4 hours.
Drain.
Cook steak as desired.

title: broccoli casserole supreme
directions: Place chopped broccoli in buttered baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spread undiluted soup over broccoli.
Sprinkle chopped onions and Cheddar cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: busy season casserole(amish cooking)
directions: Fry cubed steak and put it in a big casserole dish, then add a layer of carrots and a layer of potatoes; salt each layer to taste.
Put in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: baked chicken and nectarine salad(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice, onion powder and salt.
Cut unpeeled nectarines into large cubes.
Combine nectarines, chicken, celery, onion and noodles. Add mayonnaise mixture and mix gently.
Spoon into greased shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Spoon each serving onto lettuce leaves.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: full box party recipe
directions: Set medium size 15 3/4 x 11 1/4 x 3-inch aluminum roaster pan on a cookie sheet. Combine Crispix cereal, nuts and pretzels in the pan.
Set aside.

title: ham 'n bean skillet dinner
directions: In a medium sized skillet, heat oil, adding celery, onion, green pepper, garlic, salt and meat.
Cook until the onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the pork and beans, lima beans with liquid and chili sauce.
Do not cover.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Put the pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together the sugar, flour and eggs until mixture is crumbly. If sticky, add a little more flour. Melt the margarine and spoon over top of mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned well on top.

title: german chocolate surprise
directions: Chop nuts and spread over
greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on
box
and
spread
over
nuts.
Cream softened oleo and cream cheese.
Add box of confectioners sugar slowly.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon on top
of cake mix and bake in preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Cook zucchini until tender.
Drain. Arrange in baking dish.
Cover with hamburger.
Top with cheese. Drain tomatoes and put on top of everything.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Chop fruit and nuts; mix with 1 cup flour.
Sift together remaining flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Add fruit, nuts and flavoring; mix well.
Pour batter into tube pan, lined with brown paper or waxed paper and greased.
Place in cold oven and bake at 300°.

title: mushroom and rice stuffing
directions: Boil giblets in water (enough to cover).
Simmer until tender. When cool, shred all meat from neck and cut up remaining giblets in small pieces.
Brown onions in oil or fat, then add mushrooms and giblets.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for awhile. Add cooked rice and serve hot.
May be used as a separate dish or as a stuffing for poultry.

title: cheese quiche
directions: Spread ham and 1/2 cup cheese on bottom of pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients except butter and pour in pie shell. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup cheese over mixture and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Allow to cool for 30 minutes after baking and sprinkle nutmeg and pepper on top.

title: best cherry pie(for 9-inch pie)
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt in a medium saucepan.
Blend in cherry juice and red food coloring.
Add cherries; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture has boiled 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and almond extract.
Set aside to cool while you mix pie crust.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie plate. Cover with top crust, seal and flute edge.
Cut slits for escape of steam.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until desired brownness. Serves 8.

title: pina colada cake ii
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Instead of water use pineapple juice from the pineapple.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies (no bake)
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and butter to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add oats, Karo syrup, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet until cool.
Makes about 12 to 15 cookies.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter apples.
Roll out biscuits and place an apple piece in center.
Pull edges of dough up and pinch together at top. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Flip water over top.
Cut butter into chunks and place on apples.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken thighs with salt and 2 teaspoon poultry seasoning until done.
Crush crackers and spread part of them on bottom of buttered long Pyrex dish.
Cut chicken up and spread on top of crackers.
Melt margarine; add soup, broth and sour cream in a pot and mix well.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly (15 minutes), then cover with foil.
Cook 25 more minutes.
Remove foil and let brown.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.
Uncooked sausage balls can be frozen.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chicken torino
directions: Insure chicken is boned and pounded.
Mix all other ingredients into shallow ovenproof dish.
Add chicken and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Turn occasionally.
Heat oven to 425°. Remove 1/2 of marinade.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until done. Serve.

title: mustard dip
directions: Put in food processor; pulse 40 seconds.
Serve with vegetable plate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.

title: pineapple baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain pineapple and save syrup.
For each pound of beans, stir in 2 tablespoons brown sugar, 1 tablespoon syrup from pineapple slices, 1 tablespoon catsup and 1 teaspoon prepared mustard.
Bake in shallow casserole for 30 minutes.
Top with drained pineapple slices and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: fruit ball
directions: Thoroughly mix cream cheese, nuts, fruit cocktail, and pudding.
This can be spread over cinnamon or raisin bread for sandwiches or made into a ball and rolled in chopped nuts and served with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a round tube pan. Let cream cheese, butter and margarine soften. Beat in 3 cups sugar. Add eggs one at a time and beat. Add flour and vanilla. Beat well. Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix jello, water and sugar together until dissolved.
Chill until half solid.
Add milk and juice to jello and whip until fluffy.
Make crumbs out of wafers; put some in casserole dish, then some of fluff mixture, then little more wafer crumbs, then rest of fluff mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs and nuts over top. Refrigerate until firm.

title: boneless baked pork chop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork chops on casserole dish. Cover with soups and water.
Cook 1 hour.
Use gravy over white rice when done.

title: jello cottage cheese mold
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a mold.

title: indian pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk and molasses.
Stir in cornmeal; cook and stir until bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir for 10 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Combine egg, sugar, oleo and rest of ingredients.
Stir into hot mixture.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pink party punch
directions: Prepare powdered drink mix according to package directions. Chill. Place ice cream and strawberries in punch bowl. Pour in prepared drink. Stir. Makes 40 servings.

title: easy apple bread
directions: Mix well and add apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pureed potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Place in saucepan with salt and water to cover.
Bring to boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Thoroughly wash leeks and cut into rings.
Place leeks and a little water in separate saucepan.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Dice bacon, peel and slice onion into rings.
Puree cooked potatoes and their liquid into blender or food processor. Stir leek rings and their cooking liquid into puree.
Add hot meat stock until soup is smooth.
Stir in whipping cream.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; set aside.
Soften cream cheese and combine with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Jell-O over mixture, then fold in oranges and pineapple.
Add cottage cheese; mix well. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: wild rice-chicken supreme
directions: Prepare rice and seasoning packet according to package directions.
In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour gradually.
Stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken, parsley, cooked rice, pimiento and almonds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soup, add broth. Mix in other ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Crush 1 or 2 rolls ritz crackers. Mix with 1 stick melted margarine.
Place on top of casserole and bake at 350 F for 30 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Wash and pat dry
pork loins.
Tenderize for 1 hour, then salt and pepper on both sides.
Cut up half an onion.
Put over the meat.
Cut green pepper up and spread over the meat. Take milk and pour over each piece. Take butter and place a piece on each piece of meat.
Put in oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make gravy from drippings.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In a double boiler or microwave, melt white chocolate. Fold into cream cheese mixture with nuts.
Spread into a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Chill until ready to serve.
Cut into squares. Yields about 48 pieces.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry sausage in large skillet; drain.
Add whole tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Simmer.
In small bowl, mix cottage cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients to make soft dough. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 425° until light brown. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: santa's sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Drain.
Add to casserole dish.
Mix sugar and oleo.
Top potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until creamy.
Put one layer of mixture, then put nuts and coconut between each layer and on top. Cover with wax paper and weigh down with another dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, top with whipped cream and serve.

title: baked beans with cheese
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 1-quart baking dish for 1 hour at 400°.

title: turtles
directions: Using a well buttered plate, arrange 3 or 4 nuts in a cluster. Place 1 caramel on top of each cluster and microwave on Low until soft.
Remove and press down with a well buttered knife.
While these are cooling, melt chocolate chips, stirring constantly until smooth.
Spoon chocolate over clusters.
Let stand until firm. Remove from plate with a spatula.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in iron frying pan the sugar and Karo syrup until it spins a thread.
Add 3 cups raw peanuts and cook 15 minutes or until done and color is amber.
Remove and add 1/2 teaspoon soda. Stir and pour on greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and harden.

title: peanut butter honey puffs
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into small balls. Roll the balls in crushed cornflakes.
Place on waxed paper and chill 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: creole pinto beans
directions: In large saucepan, cover beans with water and soak overnight. Bring to boil and

cook two minutes. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 1 hour. Add tomatoes, onion, green peppers, garlic, bay leaf, salt, thyme and pepper. If necessary, add water to cover. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 1-1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are tender, adding more water if beans are dry.
Remove bay leaf and serve with rice. Serves 4.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix.
Store in airtight container.
Good for snacks, soups and salads.

title: zucchini sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage, green pepper and onions.
Remove sausage, green pepper and onions.
Saute zucchini in pan.
Mix sausage mixture with spaghetti sauce.
In a 10 x 10-inch casserole dish, layer 1/2 of the sausage mixture on bottom of casserole.
Ad cooked rice. Layer zucchini, 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese and all of the Parmesan cheese.
Add other 1/2 of sausage mixture.
Top with the rest of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: katy's french pancakes
directions: Sift flour.
Re-sift with salt, baking powder and powdered sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add and beat milk, water and vanilla.
Make a well in the sifted ingredients.
Pour in the liquid ingredients. Combine them with a few swift strokes; ignore the lumps, they will take care of themselves.
You may rest the batter refrigerated 3 to 6 hours.
Heat a 5-inch skillet.
Grease it with a few drops of oil.
Add a small quantity of batter.
Tip the skillet and let the batter spread over the bottom.
Cook the pancake over moderate heat.
When it is brown underneath, reverse it and brown the other side.
Use a few drops of oil for each pancake.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Blend soup with broth and tarragon.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange egg slices over chicken.

title: tomato rolls
directions: Dissolve the 1 teaspoon sugar and cake yeast in the warm water.
Heat to lukewarm the tomato juice, 1/2 cup sugar, the butter and salt.
Let cool.
Add the beaten eggs and 3 cups flour; beat.
To this mixture, add the dissolved yeast and beat again. Add 2 more cups flour; mix well.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour on pastry cloth; turn out dough onto it and knead.
Put in well-greased bowl; let rise.
Punch down; let rise again.
These can be made in the form of butterhorns or put in muffin tins.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes, or until light brown. Do not overbake.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine ingredients except salad oil.
Mix well.
Drop mixture by tablespoon in hot oil in a large skillet.
Flatten patties to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cook to golden brown; turn and brown other side.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Put raisins in hot water for awhile and then drain, if raisins are not soft.
Sift together sugar and flour.
You may substitute all white flour with 2 cups white and 2 cups whole wheat or 2 cups white flour, 1 cup whole wheat, 1/2 cup soy and 1/2 cup wheat germ.
Sift baking soda and salt with flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk or sour milk.
Mix all ingredients well and then fold in raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (maybe 10 to 15 minutes more).

title: glazed fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Blend sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add a few drops of red food coloring, if desired.
Cool.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar together and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° 7 to 10 minutes. Dissolve the jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Mix the cream cheese and cup of sugar and put on top of pretzel mixture.
Put the Jell-O mixture on top of cream cheese and then add Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix oranges and pineapple; add pudding mix and mix well.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: venison or beef roast
directions: Place meat in roasting pan.
Mix dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar; pour over meat.
Place bay leaves on top. Pour apple juice beside meat.
Bake 2 to 3 hours in a 350° oven.

title: cock of the walk pickled onions
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Drop in onion slices; turn heat off.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese log
directions: Mix ham and cheese well. Shape into a log and roll in pecans. Refrigerate (as long as needed). Serve with crackers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak crosswise in 1/4-inch strips and spread out on counter or board.
Apply tenderizer, if desired.

title: sausage grits casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Put in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Combine cooked hot grits, cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Gradually add beaten eggs.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spanish style baked beans
directions: Chop bacon into pan and fry until brown.
Add onions.
Cook until brown.
Add beans; stir well.
Bake 30 minutes in medium-hot oven.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together until mixed well.
Heat vegetable oil in a loaf dish.
Pour in mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 or more.

title: asparagus appetizers
directions: Take all crusts off Wonder bread slices, 40 or so.
With a rolling pin, flatten out all pieces of the bread and sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Cut asparagus in half and place one piece on each piece of bread.
Roll bread up and cut in half or thirds.
Place on seam side down onto a greased cookie sheet.
Drizzle melted margarine over the tops and sprinkle Parmesan cheese and paprika on the tops.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: double delight cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar; beat well. Beat in eggs, one at a time; add vanilla. Combine flour, salt, and baking powder; add to cream cheese mixture. Blend in raisins. Heavily grease a tube pan; sprinkle 6 Tbsp. of chopped pecans in pan. Pour batter in pan and bake at 300° approximately 1 1/2 hours. Let stand in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add water, oil and food coloring.
Cook over low heat until stiff.
Let cool and knead.
Roll into ball and store in airtight container.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dice vegetables and cheese.
Pour dressing over vegetables before ready to use.

title: belle bonne
directions: Stir by hand or use mixer. Store in dark bottles; let stand for 3 weeks.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Heat the oil in skillet.
Dip tomato slices in egg, then in flour.
Brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and cheese, if desired.
Serve hot.

title: pan liner
directions: Mix together in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Store in covered cans on shelf in pantry.
Brush on pans as needed with pastry brush.
This eliminates products (cakes, cookies, bread) from sticking to pans and reduces pan cleaning.

title: cream cheese fruit pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar.
Beat in the Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into crust and top with your favorite pie filling.

title: doughnuts
directions: Put eggs into a mixing bowl and beat very light.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add milk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add spices to flour.
Add flour to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Add flour and mix well.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet; drain hamburger.
Combine remainder of ingredients with hamburger.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients
well.
Pour
into greased skillet. Bake in 450° oven
until lightly browned.
Place under broiler to brown.

title: cracker spread
directions: In medium bowl, stir together mayonnaise, relish, and onion. Add meat, cheese and celery.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix with fork until all ingredients hold together.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: apricot baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in pan.
Mix French dressing and apricot preserves and brown gravy.
Mix, pour over chicken and marinate for 1 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: different apple salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in a dish and let set.
Top with 1 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup salad dressing and 1 cup miniature marshmallows.

title: cranberry whip salad
directions: Combine cranberries with dash of cake coloring.
Mix sugar with cranberries.
Mix cranberries, pineapple and marshmallows together and let stand in icebox for a while.
Fold in whipped topping and serve.
This will hold up to several days.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sheath cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and flour together in mixing bowl.
Combine butter, cocoa, water and shortening in saucepan; bring to a boiling point.
Pour hot liquid over dry ingredients. Add buttermilk with soda, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter into an 11 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: chocolate covered whiskey balls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup lite corn syrup and 1/2 cup bourbon.
Stir until well mixed.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Dip into chocolate chips melted with 2 tablespoons shortening (use a double boiler).
Lay out on waxed paper in refrigerator until firm.
Best if kept cold.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onion.
Mash tomatoes.
Place all ingredients in a large pot.
Add water and cook until potatoes are tender and rice is done.

title: lemon chess pie(unbaked pie shell)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugar, flour and cornmeal. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and bake 35 - 45 minutes until golden brown on top.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Use blender and mix in order given, everything except the shrimp.
Fold in shrimp last.
Serve with large Fritos.

title: strawberry-raspberry sauce
directions: Combine strawberries and raspberries and puree.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter and egg.
Press into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add liquid.
Roll in ball and put in refrigerator.
Will keep 2 weeks.
Pinch off dough for biscuit.
Bake in greased pan 425° until brown.

title: baby food plum cake
directions: Mix well and pour into floured and greased angel food cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: wagon wheels
directions: For each sandwich, use 1 hot dog and half hamburger bun.
Cut a slice of cheese into 4 squares.
Put 1 square on each bun half. Place on cookie sheet in 250° oven until cheese melts.
Cut hot dogs every inch carefully.
Do not cut clear through.
Boil hot dogs until they curl.
Place 1 on each bun.
Put a quarter slice cheese on that.
Put in oven at 400° until cheese melts.
Watch carefully.

title: mile high apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Roll 1/2 of pastry on floured surface into circle 1-inch larger than inverted pie plate.
Ease pastry into pie plate.
Combine cornstarch, Equal measure, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Sprinkle over apples in large bowl and toss.
Arrange apples in pastry. Roll remaining pastry into circle large enough to fit top of pie. Place pastry over top of pie and seal edges of pastry.
Trim and flute.

title: christmas tree cookies
directions: Cream soft butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and orange rind. Beat well.
Add flour, sifted with salt and baking powder.
You can add orange juice.
Beat until smooth.
Chill until firm.
Roll thin and cut.
Sprinkle with red and green sugar.
Bake at 300° for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Cut up 1/2 stick margarine with Velveeta cheese.
Mix with cooked broccoli.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pat's meatballs
directions: Wet the bread under water and wring out.
Mix all but last four ingredients together, including the bread.
Make a ball of the meat and dredge in flour.
Brown and drain most of the grease off.
Put meatballs in a crock-pot.
Add soup, milk or water and sour cream.
Pour this mixture over the meatballs and cook on low heat in the crock-pot.

title: ice water cake
directions: Cream well butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt and ice water. Beat 4 egg whites stiff.
Add 3 1/2 teaspoons baking powder.
Fold into other mixture.
Bake in two round 9-inch pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: beef patty made simple
directions: In a large frying pan cook ground beef.
Season ground beef to taste.
On a floured surface place crescent dough, separating parts as it is placed on the surface.
With a tablespoon, scoop up ground beef and place it on the dough.
Cover meat with dough. Pinch the ends.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Place patties on a sheet pan.
Cook until patties are browned.
Serve warm.

title: pot roast
directions: Rinse and pat roast dry.
Blend soup, wine and onion soup mix.
Put roast in large piece of heavy foil. Pour soup mix over roast.
Place potatoes, carrots, and onions around roast.
Seal foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 to 5 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: pan fried salmon
directions: Rinse and pat dry salmon fillet.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on the inside of fillet.
Press in 10 slices of garlic and 10 of ginger.
Heat oil in a skillet and stir-fry 5 slices of ginger. With the seasoned side down, pan fry the salmon until the edges are cooked (turn opaque and slightly brown).
Turn the fillet over and fry until done.
Remove the salmon from the skillet and discard the garlic and ginger.
Serve with lemon wedges or sprinkle fried salmon with finely chopped walnuts as preferred.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugar. Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in all other ingredients. Mix until completely blended.
You may need to finish mixing with your hands - mix to smooth dough.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes, until tops are slightly brown.
Cool 5 minutes on baking sheet. Remove to rack to cool. Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings.
Form into small balls. Fry in hot Wesson oil, turning frequently until light brown, but not crusty on all sides.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Mix well. Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown
chops
slightly on both sides.
Place in greased casserole
in
layers
as
follows:
a
layer of sauce, one of potatoes,
then
salt, pepper and soup.
Put pork chops on top with
a
little
of
the soup on top of them.
Bake in covered casserole
at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.
Can be used to compliment the main course or as a dessert.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no cook peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese, peanut butter (dash of salt optional) and 2/3 of Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours before serving or overnight is better.

title: casserole bean dish
directions: In casserole dish, put the can of beans and can of cream of celery or mushroom soup on top.
Put frozen onion rings on top. Bake in oven at 400° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cut
up lettuce and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble fried bacon
over
lettuce.
Slice
cooled eggs and place over bacon. Place
remaining
ingredients in layers over lettuce in this order:
celery,
onion,
water
chestnuts
and
peas.
Add sugar to Miracle Whip and spread over salad.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Drain the clams and set aside juice.
Simmer clams in small saucepan with the lemon juice.
In blender, combine green pepper, onion and 2 tablespoons of the clam juice.
Blend on medium until mix looks soupy.
To the clams, add butter and oregano.
Heat until the butter melts.
Add all the remaining ingredients including the onion/green pepper to the clam mix.
Pour into 1 or 2 pie plates and cover with the shredded cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: lemon pudding(from 1879 cookbook)
directions: Season with extract of lemon; beat well and bake in crust.

title: tuna salad bake
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup, celery, onion, mayonnaise, salt and dash of pepper.
Fold in tuna, drained and flaked, and hard-cooked eggs.
Put in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the crushed potato chips.
Bake in a hot (400°) oven for 35 minutes.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: In a large shallow bowl, layer the apples, apricots, peaches, pineapple and pears.
Mix the orange juice and lemon juice and pour over the layered fruit.
Spread pie filling evenly over fruit.

title: swedish sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Scald milk.
Mix in sugar and salt with hot milk; let cool.
When cool, pour into 4-quart bowl.
Add yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Add half of sifted flour; beat hard with mixer.
Beat in shortening (melted), rind and spice.
Add half of remaining flour; cover and let stiffen for 10 minutes, then turn onto board with rest of flour.
Knead 5 minutes.
Sweet roll dough is stickier than bread dough, so do not add additional flour.
Let rise until doubled in size in lightly covered bowl in warm (not hot) place.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In large casserole, layer sliced potatoes and sliced onions. Dot with butter (about 1/4 pound), salt and pepper.
Add milk to almost cover.
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove cover last 10 to 15 minutes to brown the chops.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Spread mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place Tater Tots in ground beef.
Add soup and milk over top of Taters.
Add enough cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Lightly grease muffin pan.
Pour into muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet-sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill several hours.
Shake again before serving over salad.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: pasta and fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells; drain.
Blend yogurt and orange juice concentrate.
Combine all ingredients.

title: cherry delight dessert
directions: Roll graham crackers fine.
Add sugar.
Melt butter and mix all together, using a fork.
Press firmly in a large 9 1/2 x 12 x 2 1/2-inch Pyrex baking pan which has been greased.
Whip the whipped cream powder according to directions.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir in cream cheese.
Spread on crumb mixture.
Add cherries over this and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together well. Place in greased pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until center is firm.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; melt oleo until soft (not hot).
Add oleo to flour and sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Have 2 uncooked pie shells.
Pour equal parts in shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
When cool, wrap in foil and put in freezer.
Whe ready to use, set out and let come to room temperature.

title: ritz pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into cracker mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with whipping cream and chill.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Debone chicken in large pieces.
Mix flour, chili powder and garlic salt.
Coat chicken pieces in mixture.
Saute onions and peppers in oil.
Add chicken and brown.
Add remaining ingredients, plus 1 cup water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low 45 minutes.
Check rice for doneness.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 450° for 45 minutes.
Holding potato with a pot holder, cut in half and scoop out the potato to form a shell. In a bowl, beat the potato pulp with butter, salt and cream until smooth.
Add onion and ham.
Pile mixture back into shell and top with grated cheese.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown beef in iron skillet.
Add cheese, onion and peppers, then beat eggs and add other ingredients to form corn bread mixture.
In iron skillet, pour a layer of corn bread mixture in iron skillet, then add your hamburger mixture and remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy cheese manicotti
directions: Spray 12 x 8-inch baking dish with Pam.
Cook manicotti to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain; place in cold water.
In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese, egg white, parsley, oregano and cayenne; blend well.
Drain manicotti or large shells.
Spoon cheese mixture into manicotti; place side by side in sprayed baking dish.
In medium saucepan, combine tomatoes, green chiles and cornstarch.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour over filled manicotti.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.
You may substitute large shells for the manicotti.

title: red hot potato salad
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Cook onion in bacon fat and add other ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and mix carefully.
Put in casserole dish.
Put in low oven to keep warm.
Garnish with parsley.

title: uncle henry's cooked custard ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add a little milk to thin the mixture.
Heat remaining milk in double boiler, then pour in the egg and sugar mixture.
Cook on medium heat until thickened and coats spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Freeze.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt oleo and stir in all other ingredients.
Serve with chicken, beef or spareribs.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper until slightly tender.
In a large bowl, mix stuffing mix, onion, bell pepper, soup, egg, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, seasonings and crab.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: fritos corn chips chili pie
directions: Crush 2 cups of Fritos corn chips and spread into a baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and half cup of cheese on Fritos chips.
Spread chili over onion and cheese.
Top with remaining Fritos corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon stuffed fish
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Sprinkle fish with lemon juice.
Place 1/2 cup stuffing on each fillet, roll loosely. Place in pan, seam side down.
Sprinkle fillet rolls with lemon juice and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Add ingredients to frozen meatballs and simmer in crock pot.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Empty into shallow baking dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer each ingredient in order listed.
Makes pie plate size.

title: date bars
directions: Cook until filling is smooth, then cool.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Make into rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice 1/8-inch thick and bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: old "testament" cake
directions: Look up in the Bible.

title: sausage and mushroom stew
directions: In an ovenproof 5-quart Dutch oven or casserole, combine all ingredients except cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and stir.
Add the cabbage.
Cover and bake 30 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Stir again before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish in layers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Chop onion, peppers and carrots.
Mix together.
Chill for 1 hour and serve.

title: apple cider mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container until ready to use.

title: apple cake with hot caramel sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Add flour, walnuts, soda and salt, mix well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-in square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares and serve with Sauce.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, sugar, pineapple juice and almond extract.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Then add cooled ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 30.

title: triple chocolate dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into a 5 quart slow cooker that has been sprayed with non-stick cooking spray. Cover and cook on low for 6-7 hours or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out with moist crumbs.
Serve in bowls with ice cream.
Or may cook on high for 3-4 hours.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine in saucepan and cook over moderate heat to soft ball stage.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Add 2 1/2 cups nuts (preferably pecans).
Spread on buttered waxed paper or cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.
Break apart and store in airtight container.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except boiling water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Put butter, mushrooms, flour and seasonings in saucepan; blend.
Add milk gradually and stir.
Cook until thickens.
Add chicken and spaghetti; heat thoroughly.
Place chicken mixture into a heat-proof platter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and brown in broiler about 7 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: Saute onions in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring often, 10-15 minutes.
Add pepper jelly and remaining ingredients, stirring until jelly melts.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Wonderful alongside black-eyed peas and ham hocks.

title: mother's salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or Cuisinart except oil. Add oil slowly with machine running.
Let sit in refrigerator 2 hours.
(Will keep for 3 days.)

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chips together. Add rest of ingredients and mix. Pour into 2 9 inch pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Alternate additions of dry ingredients, butter mixture and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in morsels.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut in pieces.
Saute onion and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons oleo until tender.
Pour in large bowl; add tomatoes, cheese and chicken.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth; add to other ingredients while hot.
Pour into large casserole.
Cook at 325° until hot.
Makes a lot and freezes well.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil.
Boil until the raisins are plump, about 3 minutes.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices together.
Cream the shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in the raisins and any remaining water.
Gradually add the flour mixture, blending thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Drop by tablespoon about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen large or 100 small cookies.

title: galloping gourmet bread
directions: Heat water to 110°.
Mix in yeast, then add remaining ingredients.
Set oven at 140°.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Make into loaf.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tempting shrimp spread
directions: Mix together and spread on finger sandwich or crackers.

title: corn pie
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch pie plate. Mix corn, egg and sugar in a bowl. Put mixture in the pan with the butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly golden brown.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Stir occasionally.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes or until dry.
Cool.
Turn out onto cutting board and add a few drops of food coloring.
Knead until color is mixed. Can allow children to mix in color when dough is cool enough. Store in airtight container.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into glass 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: *I usually use more fruit than it calls for.

title: mama's barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover and bring to a boil. Cut down and cook until meat falls apart and onion disintegrates. Stir occasionally.
Serve on buns with sliced dill pickles.
The children love it!

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Mix other ingredients with sugar water; cool and freeze.
Set out 3 hours before serving time.
Put in punch bowl and pour the ginger ale over it.
Serves 50.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix wet ingredients (first 4) well.
Arrange shrimp on lettuce, then cover with sauce.

title: honey bread
directions: Combine water and 1 tablespoon of honey.
Sprinkle yeast over and let stand until foamy.
Combine milk, oil and butter; heat to lukewarm (110°).
Place 4 1/2 cups flour in a bowl.
Make a well and add the warm milk mixture, 1/2 cup of honey and the yeast mixture.
Beat and then knead.
Continue to knead.
Continue to knead, adding more flour to make a medium dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn.
Cover and let double.
Punch down and shape into 3 loaves.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn.
Cover and let double. Punch down and shape into 3 loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans and let double.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Yields 3 (8 x 4-inch) loaves.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm water.
Add sugar, then slightly cooled margarine.
Add flour in portions as you mix well.
Bake at 375° in a greased muffin pan.

title: homemade silly putty
directions: Put glue in a plastic container.
Gradually add starch while stirring constantly.
If it is too sticky, add starch in small amounts until it feels like putty.
Store in a plastic bag or airtight container.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Pour in tube pan.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Toss berries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Sift together remaining flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Drain cooked zucchini and onion.
Toss melted oleo over croutons.
Place 1/2 of the croutons in bottom of dish.
Layer zucchini, soup and sour cream.
Top with other 1/2 of croutons. Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash lettuce and tear in bite sized pieces.
Fry bacon and remove from skillet, leaving fat to cool.
Mix onions and lettuce in a large bowl.
Crumble bacon over greens.
To the fat add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat and pour over lettuce. Toss until wilted.
Serve immediately.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place garlic and pepper in bottom of hot jars.
Wash okra thoroughly and pierce several times with fork.
Place firmly in jars.
Add dill seed.
Bring vinegar, salt and water to boil. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over okra and seal jars.
Makes about 6 pints.
Ready in 8 weeks.

title: purple cow
directions: Put all ingredients in a Blender, Mix well. Pour into glass, add ice. Enjoy!

title: clay for making holiday ornaments
directions: Put baking soda and cornstarch in a pan and mix well.
Stir in cold water until smooth.
Then cook over medium heat until the consistency of moist, mashed potatoes.
Don't overcook or clay will crumble.
Keep clay covered with damp towel.
When cool, knead it smooth.
Store in plastic bag.
Clay can be rolled out on wax paper and cut with cookie cutters to get shapes wanted for ornaments.
Use waxed paper to slide "cookies" onto a flat surface to dry overnight or until completely hard.
In damp weather it may take several days.
Decorate with paint or felt-tipped pens. Finish with spray shellac or plastic to make them more durable.

title: salted peanut bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/4 cup butter and egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over baked mixture; return to oven about 3 minutes.

title: clam fritters
directions: "Crawdad" is hillbilly for what Yankees call "crayfish." I'm hillbilly....they're crawdads.

title: tuco de carne (meat sauce for pasta)
directions: Heat oil and lightly saute onion together with garlic. Add meat, stir and fry until it changes color. Add remaining ingredients; blend well. Season to taste and simmer over low heat about 45 minutes, or until sauce is thickened. Pour over freshly cooked pasta. Serve hot.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Melt red hots and water until melted over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add apples and stir constantly until well blended. Simmer for 10 minutes. This is great on ice cream.

title: chicken-fried steak with cream gravy
directions: Cut steak crosswise into 4 pieces.
Place one piece between 2 sheets plastic wrap; using a rolling pin or meat pounder, pound to 1/4 inch thickness.
Repeat with remaining pieces.
In a pie plate with remaining pieces.
In a pie plate combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of steak first in egg mixture, then flour to coat.
Shake gently to remove excess flour.
In a skillet, melt margarine; add steak, 2 at a time.
Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes on each side.

title: muscadine jelly
directions: Boil the juice and pectin for a few seconds, stirring constantly, as it heats.
Add the sugar all at once; bring to a second boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Skim foam from top and pour immediately into hot clean jars.
Seal with paraffin.
Makes 3 small jars.

title: chocolate peanut butter parfaits
directions: Add 2 tablespoons of milk to peanut butter. Stir until well blended.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour remaining 2 cups milk into mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon half of pudding mixture into 6 parfait glasses.
Cover with topping mixture.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans and drain.
Pour into a large Pyrex dish. Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Add flour and cook until thick and smooth.
Add milk, cream, salt, pepper, soy sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Stir until thickened.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until cheese melts.
Pour this over green beans.
Add water chestnuts and sprinkle toasted almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a large pan mix and cook pudding as directed on box.
Add cake mix and stir.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 X 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle nuts over the top and bake for 30 - 35 minutes at 350.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes or until limp; drain.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each leaf.
Fold sides of each leaf over meat; roll up and fasten with toothpick or string.
Brown in hot oil in large skillet.
Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, water and lemon juice.
Pour over cabbage rolls. Simmer covered for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: chicken royale
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Salt and pepper your chicken and place in dish.
Mix soup, a little water (so soup won't be too thick), onions and Worcestershire sauce and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: reception punch
directions: Chill champagne at least 4 hours.
Combine other ingredients; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Chill well.
Just before serving, add champagne.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with a fork; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in chopped walnuts or pecans before serving.
Garnish with a cherry on top.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, syrup and salt in microwave pan and bring to a boil in microwave set on High.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda, mixing well.
Pour over popcorn (no salt or butter).
Mix to coat well.
Pour caramel corn into large brown paper bag loosely until it will fit into microwave oven.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Shake sack well after each minute.
Cool caramel corn on wax paper.
Store in 5-quart plastic container.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, baking powder, salt, and sugar. Add beaten eggs, milk and melted shortening. Beat thoroughly. Pour into a well greased pan. Bake at 425 for 25 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Layer half of eggplant, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, 3/4 cup Mozzarella and half of spaghetti sauce in a 2-quart shallow baking dish coated with cooking spray. Repeat with remaining eggplant, Parmesan cheese, 3/4 cup Mozzarella and spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 additional minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: easy stuffed shrimp
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Stir in flour and milk.
Stir constantly until thick. Add bread crumbs, crab meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook carrots, onions and celery with thyme and pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup, chicken and green beans. Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan and cover top with another pastry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Add fruit cocktail.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: reuben (sauerkraut) casserole
directions: Cook in crock pot on low for 2 to 3 hours or in oven at 325° for one hour.

title: cheese baked chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts with mallet until of uniform thickness. Arrange separately in a flat casserole.
Cover each breast with slices of cheese.
Stir soup and wine together.
Drizzle over cheese.
Coarsely crush stuffing mix.
Divide it evenly over breasts.
Pour butter in a thin stream over stuffing.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes until tender.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken breast tenders to tenderize.
Dredge pieces in beaten egg.
Cover both sides with Progresso Italian bread crumbs. Brown in small amount of olive oil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add the tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water; simmer until tender.
Add a slice of Parmesan cheese to the top of each piece.
Heat until melted.

title: baked apple rings(yield: 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Core and slice apples into 1/2-inch rings.
Place in shallow baking dish.
In a saucepan, combine and heat remaining ingredients.
Pour over apples and bake 15 minutes or until tender, turning to baste once or twice.

title: kuchen
directions: Roll mix has 2 packets.
To yeast packet, add 1 cup warm water.
To flour packet, add 1 egg and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix together to make a moist dough.
Add 3/4 cup raisins.
Knead and let stand for 1 hour.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine, brush dough and 2 round pans.
Add 1/2 dough to each pan, add fruit on top.
Make sprinkles by combining remaining margarine and 3/4 cup flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° until brown (15 to 20 minutes).
Makes 2 Kuchen.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring 2 cups water to boil.
Pour over Jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and pineapple, including juice.
Add apples and nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine and serve on bed of lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter until smooth and spread onto the pie crust and freeze 3 hours.
Before serving, top the pie with the sliced banana, whipped cream and chocolate syrup.

title: arkansas shrimp
directions: Cut breasts into 1/2-inch strips.
Place strips in medium size bowl.
Stir in salt, meat tenderizer and pepper.
Marinate 15 minutes.
Add oil and cornstarch.
Marinate 15 minutes.
Add egg whites and paprika.
Marinate 15 minutes.
Fry slowly.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Put sauerkraut in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Next, layer corned beef, Swiss cheese and tomatoes, topped with 1 teaspoon of Thousand Island dressing.
Cover with rye bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, until heated through, about 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sara's dressing
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in blender.
While running, add oil and vinegar in steady stream until thoroughly mixed and thickened.

title: herb barley soup(serves 6)
directions: Trim any fat off the meat and put it in a large saucepan. Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Skim off the top.
