Add the barley and allow to simmer for 1 hour.
Add carrots, turnips, leeks and onion; simmer for an additional hour.
Add the cabbage and season to taste with salt and pepper.
If the soup seems too thick, add a little water.
Simmer for a further 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine seasonings and tomatoes with raw meat, vegetables and tapioca in deep pan or casserole.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Don't peek!

title: potato puff
directions: Mix well
and put in baking dish and bake at 350° until brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Pat mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs; add sugar, lemon juice, 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook 1 hour at 350° or until brown.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch with cold water.
Add hot water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar and beat until stiff. Gradually add cooled cornstarch mixture.
Beat at high speed of mixer for one minute.
Spread on cooled pie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
You can use less sugar.

title: hurricane cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam; layer in bottom of pan the coconut and chopped pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and melted butter; spoon over cake mixture.
Lightly swirl into cake mixture and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: philly steak casserole
directions: In large pan, boil water. Cook noodles; drain well. Add mushroom soup. In frying pan, crumble Steak-umm, chopped pepper and onion. Drain mushrooms. Add to mixture. Cook until onions are soft. Drain. Add to noodles. Mix well. Place in crock-pot or baking dish, layering cheese and noodles, ending with cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes or in crock-pot until cheese is melted.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Dip pickles in batter and quick fry at 375° until the pickles float on top or about 4 minutes.

title: marvelous marmalade stuffing(diabetic)
directions: Mix all ingredients; toss lightly but thoroughly.
Use to lightly stuff a 4 to 5 pound bird.
Calories 261.

title: ann's cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small meatballs.
Bake at 350° in large baking pan with a little butter until done.
May be frozen before or after cooking.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine water, margarine and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Let stand.
Fluff with fork.
Cool.
Stir in pineapple, coconut, marshmallows and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip and cover about one hour.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil strawberries and 2 cups sugar 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Add 2 more cups of sugar; boil 10 minutes.
Pour into an open pan and let stand 2 days or more; berries will get thick. Can cold.

title: chocolate chip-banana muffins
directions: Do not use mixer.
Mix all ingredients with a potato masher or wooden spoon!

title: taco dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave until cheese melts.

title: nutcracker sweets
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Lay crackers side by side on foil.
Melt margarine in microwave.
Add sugar and stir. Spread over crackers. Top with nuts.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 350° or until sugar mixture is bubbly.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: texas hash
directions: Cut onion in rings. Brown in oil. Add pepper, diced fine. Add can of chopped tomatoes and stir all together on medium heat. Add cooked, drained hamburger. Add 1/2 can water and 1 cup of rice.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add oil and vanilla.
Make a paste of cocoa, red coloring and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Slowly add flour alternately with buttermilk; mix well.
Mix soda and vinegar; blend into batter.
Bake in layers for 25 minutes at 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Frost with Cream Icing.

title: dee's refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift
together	the
first
four ingredients.
In large mixing bowl,
put	shortening,
sugars
and
egg. Beat at high speed for 2
minutes.
Add orange juice, orange rind, vanilla and nuts. Blend well. Add the sifted mixture.
Beat until well blended. Shape
into
rolls. Chill overnight.
Slice thin and place on ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 or 15 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and press dough into a 13 x 9-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° until blonde, about 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked crust. Return to oven and bake 25 minutes. Cool and dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut and serve.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk, dry ingredients, nuts and lemon rind.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly, then pour the following over the loaf: 1/2 cup sugar and juice of lemon, mixed well.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and broccoli in a 2 1/2 quart microwave-safe casserole in microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes; set aside.
Blend cottage cheese in blender or food processor until very smooth.
Slowly add milk while continuing to blend.
Add chicken soup to cheese-milk mixture; blend.
Add mixture to cooked, undrained vegetables.
Microwave on High for about 3 minutes or until heated through; do not boil. Add salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dip
directions: Blend together; chill and serve with crackers.

title: easy punch
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a gallon jug; finish filling with water.
Chill or freeze to a slush.
When ready to serve, add slushy punch and bubbly (Sprite or ginger ale) to punch bowl. Very refreshing!

title: hominy casserole
directions: Heat cheese, soup and onions until cheese melts.
Stir in hominy. Pour in baking dish.
Cover with cornflakes or Fritos. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Combine butter, flour and nuts; mix well.
Press in 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: holiday bark
directions: Melt chips in microwave-safe bowl.
Spread on wax paper. Drop a topping of choice; nuts, crushed candy canes, M&M's, other, over all.
Cool.
Break apart into various size pieces.

title: pork chops & gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and banana pulp and mix well. Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Grease and flour bread pans, 1 regular or 4 miniature pans. Bake regular loaf 1 hour at 350°; miniature loaves on cookie sheet, 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini and chicken bake
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Cook bacon, onion and garlic and blend in soup.
Add	zucchini
and milk and cook until tender.
Stir in cheese, then add spaghetti and chicken and place in a 2 1/2 quart casserole.	Sprinkle
with	Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Boil 6 minutes on low heat the margarine, sugar and evaporated milk.
Add and melt marshmallows.
Add graham cracker crumbs and chopped pecans.
Spoon on waxed paper.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients
to a boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add pudding mix.
Add oats.
Mix together thoroughly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on wax paper lined tray.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix together well all ingredients.
Put in bowl and chill at least 45 minutes.
Form into ball, roll in chopped nuts and wrap in Saran Wrap. Chill.

title: vermont style baked beans (lima)
directions: Rinse beans, place in saucepan.
Add water; stick cloves into onion; add limas and boil 5 minutes.
Pour into 3-quart casserole. Let stand 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more, stirring once or twice.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add 2 cans soup, 1 can milk, chili powder and salt.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour a layer of Doritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour meat and cheese mixture over Doritos and bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: lefse(norwegian)
directions: Cook peeled potatoes until tender.
While hot, mix the following with an electric mixer:
mashed potatoes, butter, salt and cream.
Chill until cool.
(Can be kept several days in a covered container in the refrigerator.)

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer gently about 15 minutes.
Spread meat mixture into 9 x 13 pan.
Layer Mozzarella cheese and sour cream over meat. Top with crescent rolls; brush with margarine and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix and spread on cookie sheet or plate.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and grated Cheddar cheese.
Use with taco chips.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add next five ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
While noodles are cooking, mix the cream cheese, sour cream, and chopped onions. After meat cooks and noodles are done, mix all the ingredients together, except the grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese.
Put back in oven for a few seconds to let the cheese melt.

title: pastry for fried pies
directions: Sift together flour and salt, cut in shortening until mixture is consistency of small peas.
Sprinkle water over mixture.
Stir gently until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead gently.
Divide dough into ten equal pieces.
Roll each piece into 6 inch circles.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Chill all fruit; cut fruit and assemble the salad just before serving.
Layer fruit in order listed.
Sprinkle evenly with coconut and nuts.
Drizzle with honey.
Serve right away.
Contains 123 calories and 1 gram fat (0 saturated fat).

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Then add ingredients as called for. After adding them all without stirring, beat vigorously until smooth.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 8-inch layer pans. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onion in butter.
Add pimento, soup and cheese.
Add to peas and pour into casserole. Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with 1/2 bag croutons.
Mix chicken, mayonnaise, celery soup and salt.
Pour evenly into pan. Top with remaining croutons.

title: nacho dip
directions: Stir in all ingredients.
Heat in microwavable bowl for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: baked carrot custard
directions: Cover carrot pieces with water and boil slowly until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
In food processor, puree with butter and margarine for 30 seconds.
Add other ingredients and puree 30 seconds more.

title: buttermilk cake with lemon glaze
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar.
Add lemon rind and juice, salt and vanilla.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Combine flour and cornstarch.
Combine buttermilk and baking soda.
Add alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Pour Lemon Glaze over cake while warm.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Remove rind of oranges and pare off white part.
Slice fruit very thin.
Cut slices and yellow rind in small pieces.
Add lemon juice.
Measure pulp and juice and add an equal quantity of cold water.
Let stand uncovered for 24 hours.
Boil uncovered for 1 hour.
Again let stand 24 hours.
Add an equal quantity of sugar and boil until jelly is formed.
This makes a clear jelly with the fruit suspended in it.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into 2 x 3-inch pieces and place close together in a broiler pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil, turning once, until brown on both sides.
Saute onions 2 minute sin a 5-quart roaster pan.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, pineapple juice, water, salt and pepper.
Cover ribs with mixture and cover pan. Simmer over low heat 2 hours.
Remove ribs.
Thicken sauce with cornstarch dissolved in water.
Serve at once over hot, fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal apple cookies(preparation time: 25 minutes. bake time: 13 minutes.)
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco. Set aside. Cream butter flavor Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt. Mix into creamed mixture. Stir in fruit and nuts. Stir in oats. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 13 minutes. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove to cooling rack. Makes 2 1/2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: lucille's coating mix(makes 3 cups)
directions: Whirl ingredients in blender until finely crumbled.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until done.
Cool, then peel and slice and set aside.
In saucepan, over medium heat, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese, stirring, until melted.
Stir in ham.
Place 2 cups potatoes in casserole dish.
Pour ham mixture over potatoes. Arrange remaining potatoes on top.
Brush with rest of butter. Sprinkle crushed bacon on top.
Cook in medium oven until top is brown and bubbly.

title: special k loaf(dark)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs; fold in beaten eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: scallops in vodka sauce
directions: Rinse scallops and coat with lemon juice.
Heat oil and cook scallops over medium heat until half cooked.
Add tomato sauce, milk and vodka.
Cover and cook 10 minutes over low-medium heat. Add mushrooms (optional)
and heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Cook and drain angel hair pasta or pasta of your choice.
Place scallops and sauce over pasta.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken-potato bake
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender, but not brown; blend in cream of chicken soup and milk. Remove from heat; add the 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in chicken and carrots.
Pour chicken mixture into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish; arrange frozen fried potato nuggets atop casserole.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes.
Sprinkle additional shredded cheese atop casserole, return casserole to oven just until cheese melts, about 2 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 7-up salad
directions: In a bowl, mix cream cheese; add slowly, mix jello, sugar, hot water and pineapple.
Mix together and chill.

title: lime cream cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple and heat juice and water (make 1 cup liquid). Dissolve gelatin. Add cream cheese. Beat in with electric beater. Add pineapple and blend thoroughly.
Chill until slightly thickened (doesn't take long). Fold in cream which has been whipped.
Add nuts and chill again until firm.

title: fun day sundae
directions: Bottom Layer:
Prepare a day in advance so it sets up well. Crush Oreos and pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter/margarine over the crushed Oreos and mix well.
Arrange evenly over the bottom of the pan.
Store overnight.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes, or until sugar is dissolved.
Mix juice with sugar mixture.
Add bananas.
Freeze. When ready to use, chop up in a punch bowl.
Add ginger ale or Sprite.

title: italian goulash
directions: Brown ground beef, green peppers and onion.
Drain excess fat. Add all other ingredients except macaroni, cheese and parsley. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: white bean soup
directions: Cook beans and lots of water in crock-pot overnight with onion, carrot and butter. About 20 minutes before serving, add cubed ham.

title: porkiepine meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, onions and green pepper. Make into meatballs. Brown in a deep skillet. Once they are brown, pour in ketchup and water. Simmer about 45 minutes. More water may be added while simmering.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 medium size casserole dishes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Add bread crumbs to the top and brown.
Freezes very well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.
Cook in loaf pans.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients slowly.
Let stand.
Drop by teaspoon into hot shortening.
Cook until golden brown.

title: apple dumplings with red hots
directions: Roll out entire crust for 2 crust pie and place apples on top of it.
Roll up as one would for a jelly roll; cut into slices. Then place slices, side by side in baking dish and pour syrup over them.

title: pizza planks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Ask an adult to assist you in splitting the loaf of bread.
Place the bread on a cutting board.
Carefully split bread to make a slightly hollowed loaf.
Place each half on the baking sheet, cut sides up.
Spoon spaghetti, mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese evenly over the tops.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: party wings
directions: Cut wings into three pieces at joints, discarding tips (or save for broth).
Place the wings in single layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat until consistency changes (about 15 minutes).
Pour over wings and let set to marinate in refrigerator for at least 4 hours (preferably overnight).
When ready to cook, place wings, including marinade, in a 400° oven.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook for another 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix nuts, flour and butter.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Mix all at once.
Form into inch size balls.
Place in large baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Place hamburger, diced celery, onion and pepper in stewing pot.
Brown slightly.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add a little milk, if needed.
Bake at 325° for about an hour.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half crosswise and scoop out seeds.
Arrange squash, cut side down, in shallow dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn squash cut side up and spoon mixture of honey, salt, pepper, ginger, nutmeg and butter into cavities.
Continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes or until squash are tender when tested with a fork.
Serve hot.

title: garbanzo a la king
directions: Saute first
4 ingredients in 2 tablespoons water until tender.
Whiz
in
blender all except garbanzos and peas while vegetables saute.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together.
If desired, add 2 cups small marshmallows and nuts.
Freeze and serve when ready.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix egg, vinegar, sugar, flour and water and cook until mixture thickens.
Cool before pouring over grated cabbage to which has been added 1 small onion.

title: apple carrot salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sugar.
Combine apples, carrots and pecans.
Mix with dressing.
Add raisins.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix ground vegetables with salt.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Put in a pot and add all other ingredients (vinegar, seeds and sugar).
Boil about 10 minutes.
Put in jars hot and seal.

title: taco
directions: Cook beef or turkey in skillet until brown.
Pour off grease. Add water and seasoning.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Warm shells in oven at 300° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Place taco shell on plate.
Fill with layer of each:
meat, cheese, tomato, lettuce and sauce. Roll and enjoy!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Put in bottom of oblong dish (9 x 13-inch). Drain corn and chestnuts.
Layer over beans.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and mayonnaise together.
Put this on top.
Layer cheese.
Crush Ritz crackers and stir into margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: bubble solution
directions: Combine and put in an unbreakable bottle.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Gradually add vinegar, salt, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon or vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread in pie shell and bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool.
Melt chocolate chips.
Beat egg yolks.
Fold yolks and water into chocolate.
Spread 3 tablespoons chocolate mixture on meringue.
Whip the cream, gradually adding 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spread half on chocolate mixture.
Fold remaining half of cream.
Spread on top.
You will have 4 layers. Chill at least 4 hours.
This pie can be made ahead and frozen.

title: tortilla pinwheel appetizers
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, olives, chilies, onions, Cheddar cheese, garlic powder and salt well. Spread mixture liberally on each tortilla. Roll up jelly roll fashion; wrap tightly in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours. After chilling, slice each roll into 1-inch slices. Arrange on serving platter. Garnish with parsley, if desired. Serve with favorite salsa.

title: pepper relish
directions: Using blender or food processor, grate, then grind peppers. Leave juice and peppers together.
Add salt; mix and let stand for 4 hours.
Drain in colander.
Squeeze slightly to get water out. Cook sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves, then add drained peppers.
Slow boil 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir often.
Done when it looks like jam.
To can, boil jars about 10 minutes, then heat lids.
Seal.
I serve this topped on crackers spread with cream cheese.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter in a saucepan over medium heat until transparent.
Add beef; stir while cooking, until meat is light brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice and garnish with paprika.

title: no-fat death by chocolate
directions: The day before, mix mousse per directions using skim milk only.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred lettuce and add chopped onions, grated cheese, cooked ground beef and diced tomatoes.
Mix well.
Heat together the picante sauce and Catalina dressing.
Right before serving add nachos and sauce to the lettuce mixture.
This makes up a lot!

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Set caps aside.
Combine mushroom stems, onion and garlic in food processor or blender and process until finely chopped.
Heat oil in a small skillet.

Add mushroom mixture and saute over medium-high heat, 4 to 5 minutes. Return mushroom mixture to processor and add next 7 ingredients. Process until smooth, adding additional melted butter if necessary to make a smooth paste.
Set aside to cool.

title: cheese green beans
directions: Combine milk, cream cheese, salt, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese in saucepan and cook until cheese melts thoroughly.
Heat green beans in a pan and drain.
Cover with sauce and toss to coat evenly.

title: martha's biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until crumbly; add milk and egg.
Turn onto floured surface and cut out biscuits.
Bake at 400° to 450° until browned.

title: chili egg puffs
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, then add cottage cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, margarine and chilies.
Pour into 6 Bundt muffin pan.

title: hello dollies
directions: Make 4 layers over melted butter with 1 cup of each ingredient.
Drizzle 1 can Eagle Brand condensed milk over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen from sides and score.
Cool more.
Cut totally through and refrigerate.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour water over dates and soda; set aside.
Cream together sugars and butter; add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and date mixture alternately.
Stir in nuts.
Fill greased pans 1/2 full. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into a
greased pie pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° oven or until done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening; add yeast and buttermilk.
Add flour, if needed, to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead slightly.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes on lightly greased baking sheet.

title: aunt nettie's kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand 24 hours before serving.
Keeps well for several days.

title: meat loaf(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into loaf in a baking pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Can top with catsup before baking.
Pour off any fat that collected during cooking.

title: sister carol's cranberry bread coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar.
Gradually add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Empty 1/2 batter in pan.
Spread cranberry sauce and spread evenly.
Add remaining ingredients and spread evenly.
Add remaining cranberry sauce on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Remove from pan after 5 minutes.

title: rice macedon
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables for about 5 minutes.
Add soup and rice.
Pour into an ovenproof casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until rice has just soaked up soup.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer each of the first 7 ingredients in salad bowl or glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with mayo, bacon, sugar and cheese.
Do not toss until ready to serve.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Combine 1 1/2 c. mozzarella cheese, sour cream, 2 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese, and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Blend well. Spread into baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain if necessary.
Add undiluted soup and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add more ketchup or mustard according to taste.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil, reduce heat and boil for eight minutes.
Add chocolate chips, margarine and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let set at room temperature.

title: seafood treat
directions: Place block of cream cheese on plate.
Cover with crabmeat and pour cocktail sauce over all.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar and a small handful flour (less than 1/4 cup) to eggs.
Remove crusts and tear up the bread.
Mix with butter.
Add bread and butter mixture to beaten eggs.
Add the undrained pineapple.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour in buttered casserole (1 1/2-quart).

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Fluff with cream cheese until blended well. Add pineapple and blend.
Serve with orange slices and strawberries or any other fruit desired.

title: jimmy's rice
directions: For best results, do not use substitutions.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread; mix together.
Add chopped celery and onions.
Add salt, pepper and sage.
Wet with hot chicken broth.
Stir well; let sit to blend flavors.
Stir.
Add chicken broth to keep wet.
Let stand for at least 2 hours, mixing and tasting for seasoning.
Add eggs.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken livers
directions: Salt and pepper chicken livers and flour evenly.
Saute in oleo until golden brown.
Mix water and soup and pour over livers. Serve in fondue pot over low flame.

title: light batter for deep frying
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Add water and egg.
Mix until smooth.
Dip veggies or meats in batter and deep fry at 375°.

title: elsie's cheese kuchen
directions: Cut Crisco into mix of flour, baking powder, salt and sugar (if desired).
Add egg and just enough milk to make a soft dough. (Kuchen pans should be shallow, about 1-inch, but hard to find.
I use a 7 x 10 3/4 x 1 1/4-inch aluminum pan.)
On floured waxed paper, roll dough to size of pan.
Invert into pan; pat into corners and up edges.
Trim off excess.
If dough tears, just push into place.
Can dab a little water on with fingers if need to seal.
Rerolling makes it tough.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix
hot
water
and poppy seed.
Let soak while you do the next
part.
Mix
rest
of ingredients and then add poppy seed and beat
minutes.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: hidden kiss cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add extracts and egg; beat well.
Add baking powder, salt and nuts; mix until blended.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Press each ball around a Kiss so that each is completely covered.
Bake for 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 350° oven.
Do not overbake.
Cool on wire racks.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Cook turkey until pink disappears and drain.
Add squash.
Mix all ingredients.
Add 1/2 can of water and soup and mix together.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes large casserole.

title: "finikia" (melomakarona) - honey-dipped cookies
directions: With electric mixer, beat oil, butter, sugar and cognac for 5 minutes; slowly add orange juice and blend well.
Add water and baking soda; blend well.
Add cinnamon, baking powder and cloves; blend well.
Add flour slowly while stirring.
Knead until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of the bowl (add more flour, if necessary).

title: english coffee chocolate cake
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add oil, milk and hot coffee.
Next, add eggs and vanilla.

title: german potato salad
directions: Add bacon to onion; saute.
Pour off fat; add onion soup mix, vinegar, sugar, pepper and salt.

Bring mixture to a boil; mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water and add to mixture, slowly stirring constantly, until desired thickness and consistency you want. Pour over potatoes and warm on top of stove.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Refrigerate overnight or in freezer 1 hour.
Melt chocolate; dip balls.
Leave part of ball uncovered to resemble buckeyes.
Yield:
3 or 4 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Layer One:
Mix together crushed pretzels, 4 teaspoons sugar and melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown at 400° for 6 minutes.
Let cool.

title: old-fashioned creamy cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with the butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Reserve a small amount of the crumbs to decorate top.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand; do not use mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with Do Nothing Frosting.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Melt margarine, cocoa, water and buttermilk over medium heat. Stir constantly until it bubbles.
In mixing bowl, have ready sugar, flour and soda.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Batter will be very thin.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool cake thoroughly.
When cake is cool, mix creamy peanut butter and peanut oil or Wesson oil and spread on cake.

title: chickpea, pasta and spinach soup
directions: Heat oil in saucepan 1 minute.
Saute onion.
Stir in garlic, marjoram and rosemary and saute 2 minutes longer.
Add spinach; cover.
Cook over moderate heat until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add chickpeas and stock and bring to a simmer over moderate heat.
Add pasta and cook uncovered 10 minutes until pasta is tender.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown onions, green pepper and ground beef until cooked. Drain off any fat. In a 4-quart casserole which has been greased, layer eggplant, beef mixture, cheese and tomato sauce until filled.
Pour any excess sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pasta
directions: Brown beef and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except pasta and cheese.
Let simmer while pasta cooks.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Butter Bundt pan.
Stagger rolls in pan.
Mix sugar, nuts and dry pudding.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry salsa chicken
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, saute chicken in oil until browned on both sides. In a small bowl, combine the salsa, cranberries, water, honey, garlic, cinnamon and cumin; mix well. Pour over chicken. Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken juices run clear. Serve over couscous. Sprinkle with almonds. Makes 4 servings.

title: denver omelette
directions: Heat a 10 - 12 inch skillet and crisp the bacon.
Add onion and green pepper and cook to soften.
Mix tomato with eggs, pepper, cheese and tabasco.
Add to bacon/onion/pepper mix and cook on stove top over medium heat until the bottom is browned and set, (you have to look).
After bottom is set, place under broiler and cook quickly until browned, done and puffy.
Yield:
2 generous servings.

title: delight
directions: Mix this and then add 1 stick margarine (melted).
Press crust in bottom of oblong dish, 9 x 13.

title: cream of crab broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Saute onion in butter; blend in flour.
Add milk and half and half.
Stir and cook until thickened and smooth.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot soup.
Add seasonings, crab and broccoli.
Heat through.

title: peach rice pudding
directions: Drain peaches; reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
In 9-inch foil pan, mix thoroughly reserved peach syrup, the rice, water, salt and allspice.
Sprinkle dates on mixture.
Top with peach halves, cut sides up.
Place maraschino cherry in each cavity.
Cover pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Place on grill 4-inches from medium coals.
Cook 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix well.
Makes milk jug full.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft) and shape into walnut size balls.
Place meat balls in a single layer on wax paper lined cookie sheet; freeze until solid.
Store frozen meat balls in freezer bags until ready to cook.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Put butter, water and cocoa in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Pour in boiled mixture.
Add beaten eggs. Mix soda, milk and vanilla.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in an 11 x 15-inch pan.

title: ice cream parlor chocolate malt
directions: In 5-cup blender, combine milk and instant malted milk.
Blend at medium speed, stopping blender frequently to scrape sides, until instant malted milk is dissolved.
Add ice cream and chocolate cream.
Blend, stopping to scrape the sides, until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: pennsylvania-dutch filling and filled hamburg casserole
directions: Brown onion, then add celery and cook slightly to soften.
In a large bowl, tear bread into pieces.
Soak in a little milk.
Add remaining ingredients and moisten with milk to the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Bake in a casserole for 1 hour at 350° or use to stuff a chicken.

title: marinated steak strips
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch strips.
Marinate meat overnight with combined ingredients in the refrigerator.
Barbecue meat on grill (best to use wire rack).

title: italian delight
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Saute onions slightly and remove, then cook ground round until crumbly.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in baking dish and arrange noodles, meat, onions,peppers and corn in layers.
Last layer noodles.
Pour tomato soup over all.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over and return to oven to melt and brown the cheese slightly.
Serves 8.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix in DRY jello.

title: liverwurst pate
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients except the bread or crackers.
Stir to blend well.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours.
Garnish with additional parsley, if so desired.
Serve with ryes or crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, take off the
bone and toss crumbs with 1 1/2 sticks melted butter. Layer pan with
1/2 of the bread crumbs. Lay chicken on top of the crumbs.
Mix soup with 2 1/2 cans of the broth -more if too dry.
Pour this on top of chicken. Put remaining crumbs on top. Cut slices of butter on top. Cook in 375 degree oven until brown.
Use large pan or glass dish.

title: mock angel food cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Add boiling water.
Beat together egg whites, cream of tartar, baking powder and vanilla. Last, fold in egg white mixture to flour and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange supreme shortcake
directions: Peel and remove all membrane from oranges, leaving only pulp. Break into bite size pieces.
Do this over large bowl.
Juice will collect in bowl as you work.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Chill orange bits several hours.
Just before serving, melt butter over low heat, add flour and stir.
Add sugar and juice.
Cook until thickened and shiny.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Slice pound cake thin.
Put orange bits from fridge on first slice.
Cover with second slice.
Dribble hot sauce over top. Sauce can be reheated as needed over candle warmer or in microwave.

title: tarragon salad dressing
directions: Place egg in blender container or food processor.
Add remaining ingredients, except oil.
Cover and blend a few seconds. With motor running, slowly pour in salad oil, blending until smooth and thick, like mayonnaise.
Makes almost 1 1/4 cups.
Very good on chicken salad.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix soups and Cheez Whiz together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins, pecans, coconut and apple.
In a bowl, beat eggs with oil and vanilla and stir mix into flour mix until just combined.
Spoon batter into well-greased muffin pan cups, filling to top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until springy.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken well and pat dry.
Cut lemons in half.
Squeeze juice all over cavity and rub well with lemons.
Sprinkle seasoned salt in cavity.
Squeeze lemon juice all over outside of chicken and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Put squeezed lemons inside chicken.
Put oil in a pan large enough to hold chicken and put it breast side down and roast 3/4 hour.
Turn and roast 3/4 hour or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Melt and cool the Crisco shortening.
Add the sugars, eggs and molasses.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add slowly.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Form into small balls.
Roll in white sugar.
Press down with small flat-bottomed glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 325° for about 6 minutes.
(You will have round cookies as if cut with a cookie cutter.)

title: peanut butter goodies
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Press in greased 9 x 16-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bars in double boiler.
Pour over mixture.
When cooled, cut in squares.

title: venison sausage
directions: Cut venison and pork into small chunks for the grinder.
Add all the seasoning; mix thoroughly and put through the grinder using a medium blade.
Pack the meat in sausage bags or casing and hang it for long smoking at low temperature.
If you wish, the meat may be stored in freezer and used as you would pork sausage but smoking certainly adds to the flavor.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine zucchini, cereal, raisins, nuts and sugars.
Mix with fork. Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Sift over zucchini mixture.

title: pig licking good cake
directions: Drain oranges, save syrup.
Cut oranges into small pieces. Mix syrup, cut up oranges, cake mix, eggs and oil together.
Bake in three cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt nina's famous gingersnaps
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves. Cream the butter or oleo. Gradually add the sugar; cream well. Blend in molasses and egg. Add dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly. If desired, chill for easier handling. Roll out on floured surface, 1/4 at a time, to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutter. Place on lightly greased baking sheets. Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes. Remove from baking sheet immediately.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each cone.
Set cones on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Spoon Fluffy Pudding Frosting over cakes; garnish with sprinkles, if desired.
Makes 2 dozen cones.

title: nutty cole slaw
directions: In
large bowl combine all ingredients; chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half of potatoes in greased baking dish; cover with half of soup and milk mixture, then another layer of potatoes, then top with rest of soup and milk.
Top with butter and chunks of Velveeta cheese (the more the better).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cream together Criso and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk, soda and flour.
Mix until well blended. Then add orange rind, pecans and dates.
Bake in moderate oven (300° F.) for 1 1/2 or 1 3/4 hours.
Use 8-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in slow cooker approximately 6 hours.
Remove bones and skin.
Prepare rice according to directions on package. Mix chicken, rice, soup and milk together in a large casserole dish.

title: good ole potato soup
directions: *For this recipe, use 3/4 of old potatoes and new potatoes. Old potatoes cook apart faster, leaving chunks of new potatoes to "bite."

title: stromboli
directions: Roll dough out thin on lightly oiled counter top, in a rectangle shape.
Make a paste with the rest of the ingredients. Mix well and spread on bread dough up to a 1/2 inch from edges. Sprinkle with 3 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese.
Top with choice of chopped, slivered ham, pepperoni slices, onion, green pepper, mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up jelly roll style and tuck ends under.
Pinch seams down.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Slice and serve. Can top with pizza sauce before serving.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Can be served not frozen if you like.

title: orange cake
directions: *Orange rind is optional.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Good served with honeydew melon or toasted for breakfast.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Mince shrimp.
Add water chestnuts, salt, sugar, 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 egg.
Beat egg white and blend in 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into 4 triangles. Brush one side of bread with egg white mixture and then shrimp paste.
Fry shrimp side down in 375° oil until golden.
Carefully turn and brown bread side.
Drain.
Serve hot.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Makes 12 servings at $1.01 each. Prep: 30 minutes. Cook: 8 minutes. Refrigerate: 24 to 48 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add
alternately
with
milk.
Add	vanilla.
Pour	into greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until it has lost red color.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: granola
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Add oil, water and vanilla and mix well again.
Bake for 2 hours at 225° or until golden brown. Stir often while baking.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until transparent.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Top with buttered cornbread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: egg toast
directions: Fry eggs in a pan.
Toast bread while frying eggs.
When done, put eggs on toast.
Put 2 teaspoons of sour cream on each piece of toast.
Add 2 tablespoons of salsa.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Enjoy.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and cook 30 minutes.
Cook orzo and add to first mixture and cook 10 minutes more.

title: mom's mincemeat
directions: Pare, core and chop apples.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Add cider to moisten (about 3/4 gallon).
Simmer until meats and fruits are tender and flavors are blended.
If desired, any other fruit juice may be substituted (cider is best). Pack in freshly sterilized jars and process in canner to seal. May freeze in Ziploc bags.
Bake pie at 375-425° for about 25 minutes.

title: chestertown crab dip
directions: Any ingredient may be lite or fat-free version.
Soften cream cheese.
Add mayo, sour cream, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until no lumps remain.
Stir in wine and seasonings. Fold in crabmeat, eggs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: country skillet pork
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch cubes.
Coat with mixture of cornstarch, pepper and garlic powder.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add pork and brown on all sides.
Remove pan from heat.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl well.
After well blended, pour into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to the following.
In large bowl, combine sugar, egg, oil, salt and flour.
Beat until mixed well.
Mixture will be soupy.
Cover bowl and refrigerate until needed. Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not let rise.

title: no bakes
directions: Heat to rolling boil the sugar, milk and chocolate.
Cook exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Let set and store in tight containers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350° until done. Grate cheese on top and cover.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and vanilla together, then make into little balls. Put in refrigerator until dip is done.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Make into small balls.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Brown meatballs in bacon fat.
Remove meatballs.
Melt margarine in pan, then add flour.
Stir until well blended; add broth gradually, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add meatballs and cover.
Simmer for 3 hours on low heat.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Serves 5 to 6.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine and boil hard for 1 to 2 minutes (until consistency is firm) the sugar, margarine or butter and milk.
Then remove from heat and add the oatmeal, cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well; drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: fruit cake ii
directions: Combine eggs, mincemeat, condensed
milk,
fruit and nuts. Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into
pan.
Use
a
9-inch spring-form
pan, butter it.
Line it with wax paper
and butter again.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until center springs
back when
touched and top is golden. Cool;
turn out.
Remove paper.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O in a microwave bowl and heat 2 minutes to dissolve Jell-O. Cool completely. Add buttermilk. Fold in Cool Whip until well blended. Store in covered container in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine first three ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda. Pour over popped corn (and nuts) in large roasting pan, stirring to coat.
Bake at 250°, uncovered, for 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.
Store in airtight container. Makes 5 to 6 quarts.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Spread rolls in a 13 x 9-inch pan or glass dish.
Top with sausage that has been browned and crumbled.
Sprinkle with cheese. Beat eggs and green peppers, salt, black pepper and oregano. Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: avocado chili spread
directions: Mash avocado thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Refrigerate.
Serve as a dip or spread with crackers or chips.

title: dan's homemade pina colada ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into a one gallon ice cream freezer and finish filling with whole milk.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Dot top of corn with 2 tablespoons of butter. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown around edges.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients and place in a pan.
Put cut up chicken on the top and bake in a 350° oven about an hour or until done.

title: fruit of the sea
directions: Mix everything, except flour, in shallow casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over and mix well.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and butter in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until melted. Continue cooking until light syrup, about 5 minutes. In deep bowl, mix slightly beaten egg yolks, flour, cornstarch and milk. Gradually add to sugar and butter mixture, cooking on low heat until thickened.
Add peanut butter; stir well. Place in cooked pie shell; cool. Top with whipped topping. Chill. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Put milk in double boiler.
Add chocolate.
Mix sugar, salt and flour and add to chocolate mixture.
Add egg yolks.
When thick, remove from fire.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pastry shell.
Make meringue by beating 2 egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar until mixture stands in peaks.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square dish.
Set aside.
Place confectioners sugar and cocoa in a medium microwavable mixing bowl. Stir to combine.
Add milk and sugar-cocoa mixture.
Do not stir. Heat, uncovered, on Full power 2 minutes.
After cooking, stir just to combine ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Pour into prepared dish and refrigerate 1 hour before cutting and serving.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown the hamburger in a heavy skillet; pour with the other ingredients into a heavy saucepan. Simmer for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until celery is done. This can be frozen.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Combine drained fruits, bananas and apples.
Set aside. Combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate.
Beat until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill.
Can be served in lettuce cups.

title: low calorie, low cholesterol chicken
directions: Spray wok with Pam. Add a little butter or cooking oil.
Put the chicken pieces in the hot wok.
Season
with lemon pepper and poultry seasoning. Cook chicken.
Remove chicken from wok.
Put frozen vegetables in the wok and cook.
Add chicken.
Heat. Serve over rice. Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Cover apples with cinnamon and sugar in an ungreased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Easy and delicious!

title: laurie's pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 1/3 c. sugar.	Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 6 minutes (not to brown).
Let cool. Then mix cream cheese, 1/2 c. sugar and pineapple together.
Fold in cool whip and chill.
Fold in pretzels just before serving.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: *All to equal 3 cups.

title: people puppy chow(appetizer, snack)
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat the egg yolks, milk, sugar and cornstarch.
After it's thickened, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Whip egg whites and sugar to a peak.
Spread over filling.
Place pie under broiler until golden brown.
Refrigerate.

title: snowdrop cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla; beat until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased foil-lined cookie sheets and bake in preheated 250° oven for 25 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cookies 30 minutes more. Outsides will be hard; insides will be slightly soft.

title: potato pancakes - latkes
directions: Peel the potatoes and rinse them.
Grate the potatoes finely by hand on a grater.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Heat 1/2 cup of vegetable oil in a frying pan until hot.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of the potato mixture into the hot oil and brown on both sides.
Serve with sour cream.

title: butter brickle cake
directions: Mix pineapple, pie filling and brown sugar and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine and mix in cake mix. Crumble over top of fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 10 x 9-inch pan or iron skillet for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, nuts and strawberries.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: herbed beef rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place meat on rack in shallow roasting pan. Combine seasoning, salt and black pepper; press evenly into surface of meat. Roast, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes per pound or until internal temperature reaches 145° for medium-rare or 160° for medium. Add water to baking pan after 1 hour of bake time to use for drippings. Remove roast from oven and transfer to platter or carving board. Let stand 10 minutes before carving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy chicken
directions: Mix together onion soup mix, preserves and dressing.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chili con queso(dip)
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes and chiles.
Cook 20 minutes over medium heat.
Lower heat and blend in cream cheese.
Add spices to suit your taste.
Mix well. Heat through and serve warm with Sam Choice tortilla chips.
This reheats well in microwave.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all except oil.
Shape into small balls; place on cookie sheet in 345° oven until done, well browned, then remove from pan and put into sauce.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Combine chocolate, marshmallows and milk.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, until mixture is melted.
Cool completely.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold chocolate mixture in.
Spoon into crust. Chill several hours.
Serve with pie filling drizzled over each piece.

title: pukalani snow peas
directions: In hot wok, add oil, garlic, onion, water chestnuts and mushrooms for 4 minutes.
Add peas, soy sauce, water and sugar. Stir.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 5 minutes or until peas are tender but crisp.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and beaten eggs thoroughly. Add milk and vanilla. Stir. Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix well. Put about 1/4 cup flour on top. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Have fat hot.
Roll out about 1/2-inch (use small amount of flour).
Let rise in fat; turn over quickly.
Drain on brown paper bags (2).

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Bring vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper to a boil.
Pour over beans, onion and green pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps several days.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in frypan.
Add minced onion; stir until wet and brownish.
Pour into casserole.
Add consomme and rice. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring to boil; add Jell-O.
When dissolved, cool until jellied, then whip.
Blend in cream cheese, Miracle Whip and sugar.
Fold in cubed chicken, carrots, celery and drained pineapple.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until ready to serve (overnight if possible).
Serve.

title: chocolate decadence
directions: Line an 8 inch cake pan with parchment.
In a saucepan, combine butter and chocolate until melted; set aside.
In a separate saucepan, combine eggs and sugar and heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture darkens.
Beat eggs until triple in volume; fold in flour.
Carefully stir 1/2 egg mixture into chocolate.
Fold in rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pan and bake at 425° for 15-20 minutes.
Cool in pan and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Use long loaf pan.
Spread pie filling and then pineapple. Spread dry cake mix on top of cherry and pineapple.
Spoon melted butter on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and then nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry
ingredients
together.
Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and egg well.
Add	flour
mixture	to
creamed mixture. Mix well. Chill for 20
minutes.
Dust
with
enough flour to handle well. Roll
into	balls.	Place
on
ungreased
cookie sheet; dip the bottom of a glass in
sugar
and mash them out. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: paulette's pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges until well blended.
Prepare 3 round cake pans, lined and greased.
Bake cakes at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: angel food cake and filling
directions: Bake angel food cake according to package directions.
Cool. Cut cake into 3 layers.

title: basil cream sauce
directions: Saute butter, shallots and garlic, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
Add basil, parsley, wine, cream, lemon juice, pepper and salt.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is reduced to about 1/2 (stir frequently).
Taste for seasoning, adding pepper and salt as needed.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add meat and rest of ingredients in large pot.
Cook on low until all of the cheese melts.
Serve warm with nachos or Frito chips.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Put into a large bowl the lard, water, egg white and salt. Add flour; stir quickly with a knife.
Keep stirring until almost stiff enough to roll out.
Turn out onto a kneading board; mix in a little more flour and work into a smooth dough.
Divide into pieces the right size for one crust.
Roll out the dough, then line the pie pans.
If any is left, make out into tart shells.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for about 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Tear flour tortillas into bite size pieces and saute in olive oil.
Mix salsa, garlic powder, sour cream and onion together for sauce.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: stuffing
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 300°.
Melt margarine.
Put layer of thinly sliced potatoes, layer of grated carrots, layer of onion, beef, salt and pepper to taste and soup.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add grated cheese and let melt.

title: betty's sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: yummy meat loaf
directions: Put ground beef into mixing bowl. Add egg, V-8 juice, onions and oatmeal. Lightly sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients together with hands until blended and soft.

Form into large ball and transfer to metal or glass baking dish (8 x 8 x 2 1/4-inch). Pat to flatten. Lightly salt and pepper top of meat loaf. Turn oven on to 400°. Put meat loaf in for approximately 10 minutes to allow it to get firm, then cover top with ketchup. Cook for an additional 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Gradually add milk to salad dressing mix until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add pecans.
Mix.
Make hole in middle of dry mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in hole.
Stir enough to dampen ingredients.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix taco sauce and French dressing together.
Mix all ingredients just before eating.
Put taco chips in very last thing.

title: cheesy moon bread
directions: Generously grease a 12-inch pizza pan. In large bowl, mix warm water with yeast from hot roll mix; stir until dissolved. Stir in egg, butter and seasonings. Add flour from roll mix, cheese and olives. Stir until well blended.

Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes. Knead dough on well floured surface, about 10 strokes. Shape dough onto prepared pizza pan. Cover; let rise in warm place 30 to 45 minutes. Slit top of dough 3 to 4 times. Brush with beaten egg, if desired. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown. Remove from pan.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix 2/3 to 1 cup sugar and cornstarch together.
Add water and fruit and bring to a boil.
Put in 8 x 8 inch shallow baking dish and dot with butter.
Mix flour, salt, 1 to 3 Tbsp. sugar and baking powder together and then cut in oleo and stir in milk. Drop by teaspoon over hot fruit.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Add mayonnaise to Dream Whip; blend well.
Add fruit cocktail, banana and maraschino cherries.
Add coconut, nuts and as many marshmallows as desired.
Put in freezer until a few minutes before ready to serve.

title: pretzel dancers
directions: In a big bowl, mix together yeast, water, sugar and salt. Stir in flour; knead on table until dough is smooth. Shape dough into dancer shapes or other preferred shape.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake in oven set at 425° for 15 minutes or until browned.
"These are fun for kids to make!"

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box, except use 1 1/2 cups fruit liquid instead of milk.
Cool.
Stir in fruit.
Refrigerate until served.

title: chicken-n-dressing casserole
directions: Mix broth and soup together and bring to a boil.
Pour dressing in and mix.
In a large casserole dish, start with dressing, then chicken, ending with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, sour cream, butter and eggs. Bake until done at 350°. Let cool and crumble in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Add one layer at a time the peas, onions, pepper, tomatoes and pickles. Top with 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon sugar, mixed well. Then sprinkle with the cheese.

title: deb's party chex mix
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in a grocery bag.
Melt margarine and add spices.
Pour evenly over chex mix and mix well. Microwave for 3 1/2 minutes on high, 4 times, shaking well after each cooking period.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, butter and sour cream.
Cook over medium or low heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat by hand until thick. Pour all at once onto a buttered platter.
Top will be glossy and uneven.
Cut when firm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add flour and milk together, then sugar; beat well.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Warm butter; put in mixture.
Heat mixture until thick.
Pour over vanilla wafer and banana (sliced) layers.
Cover and cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Roll biscuits in dry pudding and put in pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar in pan.
Then pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes let cool 3
minutes then turn over on a plate.

title: mongolian beef
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut beef with grain into 1/8-inch slices. Toss beef, cornstarch, 1 tablespoon oil, the salt, sugar, 1 teaspoon soy sauce and the white pepper in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut green onion into 2-inch pieces.
Heat wok until 1 or 2 drops of water bubble and skitter when sprinkled in wok.
Add 3 tablespoons vegetable oil; rotate wok to coat side. Add ginger root and garlic.
Stir-fry until brown.
Add beef; stir-fry until beef is brown, about 3 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon soy sauce; stir to coat beef.
Add green onion.
Stir-fry 30 seconds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter until soft. Stir in flour. Add water. Cook on low heat, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Blend in cheese. Combine sauce and broccoli. Add eggs; mix gently until blended. Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with crumbs. Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Turn on broiler for a few minutes to brown topping.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, butter, lemon juice, egg yolks, milk and lemon rind in saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into pie shell.
May top with whipped cream or meringue, if desired.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals.
Then slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks. Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.
Combine the egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add the potatoes.
Mix to coat.
Pour the coated potatoes onto the cookie sheet.
Spread them into a single layer, leaving a little space between them.
Place the cookie sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until the fries are crispy, turning them every 6 to 8 minutes with a spatula so they brown evenly.
I added cubes of squash and zucchini coated with sauce the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Then roll chicken breast in mixture.
Then add chicken to bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not cover while baking.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 325°.

Have ready a shallow 3-quart baking dish. Mix all ingredients, except bacon, in a large bowl until well blended. Pour into casserole and top with bacon slices. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours until juices have thickened.
Makes 20 servings.
Each serving contains 230 calories and 6 grams fat.

title: squirrel stew
directions: Cook squirrels in crock-pot until cooked off bone.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oil on all sides; remove and set aside.
In same oil, brown onions, remove and set aside.
Add flour and cook until dark brown and well blended.
Add bouillon, wine and tomato paste.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Return roast and onions to pot.
Add bay leaves, thyme and rosemary; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and place in a 350° oven for 3 hours.
Remove bay leaves and discard.
Serve with small new potatoes and carrots. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Beat cream.
Stir in cocoa.
Add hot fudge sauce.
Pour into sherbet cups and top with bitter sweet chocolate sprinkles.

title: zap an apple
directions: Wash and dry apples; insert stick into stem end of each apple. Microwave caramels and water in small deep glass bowl on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring after each minute until sauce is smooth.
(If caramel sauce is too thin, let stand about 2 minutes before dipping apples.) Dip apples into hot caramel sauce; turn until coated.
Scrape excess sauce from bottom of apples.
Place on greased wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving to allow caramel to soften. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: henry ford estate reuben bake
directions: Cook, rinse and drain noodles.
Place noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Toss noodles with the butter.
Spread sauerkraut over noodles.
Shred corned beef and mix with dressing.
Cover sauerkraut with corned beef and dressing mix.
Layer tomato slices and cheese over the beef mix. Melt remaining butter and combine with crumbs and seeds.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake about 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat cream and butter.
Do not boil.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Serve over pasta.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 5 minutes; set aside. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Add the cooled raisin mixture and nut meats. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by a teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake in hot oven, 350°, for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Work real good all ingredients and put all dough in Tupperware bowl.
Cook as needed.
Grease pan.
Turn biscuits in grease. Put in cold oven.
Turn to 450°. Bake approximately 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown sausage.
Crumble meat into small pieces.
In large pot, combine sausage, plus all remaining ingredients; bring to a simmer on low heat.
Cook, stirring every 15 minutes, for 2 to 3 hours. Top with grated cheese and chopped onion.
Serves 12.

title: pimiento cheese dip
directions: Puree Ricotta cheese with the Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, onion and salt.
Stir in cheese and pimiento.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Stir all ingredients well.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma dee's chewy bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes!

title: cherry fluff
directions: All ingredients must be refrigerated and cold.
Take milk and beat it 5 minutes in large bowl.
Drain pineapple and squeeze out juice.
Fold in pineapple and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.

title: pastor mark's microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, egg, spaghetti sauce, bread crumbs, pepper, garlic powder, minced onion and salt in a large bowl and mix well. Place in a loaf pan.
Cook on full power for 3 minutes.
Mix catsup, mustard, worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Pour over meat loaf.
Return to microwave and cook on level 3 for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes with a fork.
Mix all ingredients together. Spread in a pie plate or other flat dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Carr's water crackers.

title: "dump" cake
directions: "Dump" your choice of fruit into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Dump dry cake mix over fruit, spreading evenly over fruit. Thinly slice butter and place evenly over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Ice cream and whipped cream is good with this.

title: macaroni-chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Drain peas and pimentos. Add this to the chicken with broth. Break up pieces of chicken. Add pickles and a little mayonnaise at the time. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread(makes 2)
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, nutmeg, baking soda and baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix and add eggs (beat until frothy), sugar, brown sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add to total mixture the grated zucchini, walnuts, raisins and pineapple.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage, bread crumbs, egg and Parmesan cheese. Form into 1-inch diameter meatballs.
Brown in skillet until cooked through.
In separate saucepan, melt the grape jelly on low heat; add chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce and remaining ingredients.
Heat and combine with meatballs.
Serve warm.
Makes approximately 40 (1-inch) meatballs.

title: baked beans
directions: In large pot on medium heat, saute bacon pieces.
Do not to cook them all the way.
Add green peppers; saute until they start to soften.
Add onions and saute until transparent.
Add the beans and brown sugar.
Add whatever else you think would taste good (ketchup, honey, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, hickory smoke, etc.).
Add seasonings to taste (garlic, onion powder, seasoned salt, etc.).

title: divinity
directions: Boil first three ingredients until it forms a firm ball between your fingers.
Pour half over stiffly beaten egg whites. Return other half and boil until it forms a hard ball between fingers.
Pour rest over the mixture and beat until it stands in peaks or holds its shape.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chopped liver
directions: Saute livers in oil and boil the eggs.
Drain the liver and then grind alternately eggs, liver and onions.
Add salt to taste.

title: zesty salmon
directions: Mix lemon (juice and pulp), soy sauce, vinegar, seasoning and mustard.
Marinate salmon 1 hour.
Fry 7 to 10 minutes per side in hot oil in frying pan.

title: refrigerator pickle
directions: Mix cucumbers, celery, green peppers, onion, red peppers and salt in large non-aluminum bowl.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain well.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
For crust, combine cake mix; keep out 1 cup.
Combine with 1 egg and oil in a large bowl (mixture will be crumbly).
Press into bottom of pan.

title: noodle pudding(kugel)
directions: Mix last 2 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cook noodles.
Slice apples.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients (except last 2) together. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Beat together butter, egg and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in Queen Ann cherries and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, warm or cold.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan or top of double boiler, cook milk and chocolate until chocolate melts, whipping with wire whisk until blended.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add gradually to chocolate mixture.
Cook until it thickens and boils, stirring constantly 6 to 7 minutes.
Beat egg yolks.
Remove the pan from the heat and gradually add a little of the chocolate mixture to egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Then add it back to the mixture in the saucepan.
Continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes or until nicely thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and butter. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: chicken with lemon
directions: Skin and remove bones from chicken.
Rub oregano, salt and pepper into chicken.
Place in a covered casserole.
Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 minutes.
You may remove cover for last 10 minutes to brown, but meat may dry out. Spoon juice over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: super dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients except wieners in a deep bowl.
Batter should be smooth and slightly thick.
Dip wieners in batter and deep fry in a saucepan with about 4 inches of Crisco until golden brown.
Serve with mustard as you would a corn dog.

title: veal parmesan casserole
directions: Break spaghetti pieces in half.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Pound veal pieces to 1/4 inch thick.
In shallow dish combine flour, salt, and pepper.
In another dish combine egg and milk.	In a third dish mix bread crumbs and 1/3 cup parmesan cheese.
Coat veal with flour mixture; dip in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In large skillet brown meat on both sides in hot oil, 2 or 3 pieces at a time; remove from heat, reserving drippings in skillet.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan 35 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned hot milk cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter to milk; keep hot.
Beat eggs until lemon colored, about 3 minutes at high speed with mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly at medium speed for 4 to 5 minutes.
Quickly add the sifted dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir until blended; add hot milk mixture and vanilla.
Pour into floured tube pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 15 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add pepper, onion, pineapple, seasoned salt and 1 cup nuts.
Mix well and shape into ball.
Roll in 1 cup nuts.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: roasin yers*
directions: Remove the shucks from the corn.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.
Keep turning them over until they brown evenly.
Remove from oven and take a stick of margarine and rub over each ear. Salt to taste.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve as a dip for assorted fresh vegetables.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 cups.

title: caramel corn
directions: Prepare 6 quarts of popped corn first.

title: grandmammie's chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Boil and stir constantly for 1 minute only.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir to cool and achieve spreading consistency.

title: kelly's graham cracker cookies
directions: Line long baking pan with foil.
Lay graham crackers on foil.
Melt margarine with sugar and boil (full) for 2 minutes or until the mixture changes color.
Pour over crackers and sprinkle chopped nuts over this.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and break crackers and enjoy!
