title: chicken crunch on ham
directions: Roll chicken in the combined mushroom, milk, onion and parsley, then in finely crushed Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Butter baking dish or shallow pan.
Place slices of ham in pan, then boned chicken on each piece of ham.
Melt butter and spoon over each piece of chicken.
Cover with foil, punctured to make holes the size of colander holes.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Can be prepared for baking a day in advance.
Serves 8.

title: dirty rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
Put all ingredients in a casserole dish. Stir well. Cover the dish and bake about 50 to 55 minutes in oven at 425°.

title: birthday cookie
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Beat together firmly packed brown sugar and butter until light.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in uncooked oats, semi-sweet chocolate pieces and chopped nuts.
Divide dough in half.
Spread each half to 3/4-inch thickness on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes two 11-inch cookies.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind berries and mix all together.
Let stand in refrigerator until ready to use.
Then mix with whipped cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Place mixture in 12 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes. Beat eggs, sugar and 2 sticks of margarine until creamy.
Pour into baked crust.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries. Serves 6.

title: "asparagus and peas to please"
directions: Drain liquid from peas, asparagus and water chestnuts. Cut water chestnuts in bite size pieces. Mix peas, asparagus, water chestnuts and mushroom soup together. Place in greased casserole dish and cover top with crushed saltine cracker crumbs. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cracker crumbs are lightly browned.

title: renee's homemade tartar sauce
directions: Dice pickles and onion as fine as possible.
Add juice and mayonnaise.
Serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Will also need a regular salad bowl.

title: pink peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook 5 minutes the sugar and milk.
Add fluff, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan (8 x 8-inches).
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion in margarine in large saucepan until tender.
Stir in biscuit mix, pepper and thyme.
Add chicken broth and evaporated milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Heat until bubbly; reduce heat and keep warm.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and Cool Whip thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill.
May substitute lite cherry pie filling and fat-free/nonfat plain yogurt instead of Eagle Brand.
This makes the salad not quite as rich but still good.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add shortening, buttermilk, mashed bananas, eggs and nuts.
Mix all together until well blended.
Serves 10.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and peanuts in 3-quart saucepan, mixing well.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Beat in butter, vanilla and food coloring until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; shape into patties.
Cool until firm.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add water and cook on medium heat until thickens. Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla. Stir. Serve hot over biscuits.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Oven should be at 375°.
First, you should mash potatoes, then add butter.
Next, add egg, then sugar.
Last, add nutmeg.
Then beat all of the ingredients together until all lumps are gone. For last, blend with cake mixer to get strings out.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs in top of double boiler. Gradually stir in sugar, flour, salt, water and lemon juice. Cook until mixture thickens, then add margarine.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with margarine and brown in a 375° oven.
Makes 1 pie.

title: fondue au chocolat
directions: Combine in fondue pot the chocolate with the whipping cream. Stir over low heat until chocolate is melted. Add the vanilla. Mix well.

title: stuffed cube steaks
directions: Saute onion and celery in 4 tablespoons margarine for 5 minutes.
Remove
from
heat.
Add
stuffing
mix
and toss to blend.
Spread 1/3 cup mixture over each steak.
Roll starting with narrow end. Secure with toothpicks.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in order and chill overnight.

title: crab rangoons
directions: Mash crabmeat with a fork.
Blend in cream cheese.
Drop small spoonful in center of wonton wrap.
Moisten edges to seal and fold to a triangle.
Heat oil in wok or deep fryer.
Drop crab rangoons in oil turning once just until lightly golden brown.
Drain and serve with LaChoy red sweet and sour sauce.
Serve immediately. Makes 20 to 30.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Flour chicken, then lightly brown in frying pan well (2 cups of oil).
Remove chicken and place in a plate.
The remains in the frying pan, place in a large pot.
Add 4 tablespoons of oil, a layer of onions, chicken and seasoning, and repeat until all used. Add water to pot; cover half of chicken and onion layers.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add water if needed, a little at a time, so chicken does not burn.
Enjoy.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hershey's light chocolate cake(160 cal., 4 grams fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 2 round pans with cooking spray. In bowl, stir flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In saucepan, melt light corn oil spread.
Stir in sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, vinegar and vanilla to mixture in saucepan.
Add dry ingredients.
Whisk until well blended.
Pour evenly into pans. Bake 20 minutes.

title: polka-dot rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring broth or stock to a boil.
Add rice.
Simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Stir in peas and butter or margarine.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time is 25 minutes.

title: deli rye and cheese bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; mix well.
Add cheese and mix well.
Combine egg, oil, milk and honey.
Mix well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until just blended.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa; add milk and stir until blended.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Whip about 50 strokes.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool, then cut.

title: sweet chicken with apples
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Stir-fry onion and carrots in oil until tender.
Add chicken.
Combine cornstarch, bouillon and cinnamon.
Stir in apple juice and vinegar until thoroughly combined.
Add to chicken mixture.
Stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Place apple rings on top of chicken.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 3 minutes.
Place hot rice on platter.
Top with chicken and apples.
Arrange apples around.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: corn dodgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use small amount of oil in Teflon skillet and heat until hot.
Pour 1/4 cup batter in skillet for each corn dodger.
Brown and turn, about 3 minutes on each side. Add oil as necessary to fry all of them.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all except raisins, margarine and vanilla. Cook and stir the pudding mixture until thickened. Add raisins, margarine and vanilla. Stir in.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch crust glass pie pans.
Top with crust strips.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bean and macaroni soup(pasta fagioli)
directions: Brown onion, garlic and celery in olive oil until soft and transparent.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil; add macaroni.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes, covered, or until almost tender.
Add beans with their liquid.
Cover and cook for another 5 minutes, or until macaroni is tender and beans heated through.
Serve with grated Parmesan and Romano cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cucumbers
directions: Peel and cut cucumbers into thin slices.
Finely chop green pepper.
Finely chop onion.
Combine cucumbers, green pepper and onion in container (jar). Sprinkle on salt and celery seed. Stir and let stand 1 hour. Combine 3/4 cup sugar and vinegar.
Mix and pour over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate. Ready to eat in 1 day.

title: ham, broccoli, noodle, cheese casserole
directions: In a large frying pan, saute onions in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add ham and stir and continue cooking for 1 minute.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oatmeal and sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Pat 2/3 of mixture into 11 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Spread with apricot preserves and crumble remaining mixture on top.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: blondies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased shallow pan in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: black bean, corn and bell pepper salad
directions: Drain beans and cover with fresh water.
Cook for 1 hour or until tender.
Cool beans and drain.

title: mom's appetizer cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add other ingredients, using only 1 cup of the nuts.
Mix well and chill.
Shape into either one large or two medium balls.
Roll balls in remaining nuts.
Best made a day or two before serving.
Cut recipe in half, if needed.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Chop asparagus, setting aside tips for use later.
Simmer chopped asparagus and chopped potato in 2 cups water with 2 tablespoons butter, basil, celery salt, vegetable salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Cool.
Place cooled broth and vegetables in blender and puree, slowly adding the 2 cups of milk.

title: pork chop and hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl; mix well. Add 1/2 cheese, potatoes and onions; mix well. Spoon into 9 x 13 pan.

title: teething biscuits
directions: Mix flour, cereal and sugar in bowl.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle with milk; stir thoroughly.
Knead dough 15 times with hands. Make 3/4-inch balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls to 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: pizza rice cakes
directions: First, place rice cakes on baking sheet.
Second, spread sauce evenly.
Third, top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla; fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in unbaked pie shell 25 to 30 minutes or until glazy on top.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Melt the 2 tablespoons oleo in the baking dish, 9 x 13 x 2-inch and pour over the 1/2 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons cinnamon, 1 tablespoon flour and chopped walnuts.
Set aside.
Your baking pan is already greased for you.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Place milk, sugar, salt and butter in saucepan; heat to lukewarm.
Pour in bowl; add yeast and then flour.
Mix well and set in warm place for 15 minutes. Pour out on floured board and pat to 1-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter; fold over bits of butter (this will take about 2 or more tablespoons of butter).
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise 15 minutes in a warm place.
Place in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: caramel oatmeal bars
directions: Cream
margarine
and
brown sugar; add whipping cream, then rest of ingredients.
Take out 1/3 of dough and save for top.
Pat 2/3 of dough in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and do not salt. Melt 1/2 stick oleo with cheese. Mix together. Top with Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick melted oleo. Sprinkle with garlic powder and bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin(serves 4 to 5 people)
directions: Boil and cut up potatoes in julienne pieces.
In a saucepan, over low heat, combine shredded Cheddar cheese and butter.
Stir occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, scallions, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over potatoes and blend together (don't break potatoes).

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip. Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in milk, vanilla and eggs. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Gradually beat into butter mixture. Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheet. Flatten and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: beef goulash
directions: Cook onions in oil.
Cut beef into cubes and sprinkle with vinegar.
Add salt, paprika and cooked onions. Cover and simmer about 3 hours.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cream sugar and butter and then beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Sift flour, cocoa and baking powder together.
Add alternately with buttermilk in the first mixture. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 5 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Icing.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil all together for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: stuffed brisket
directions: Trim and make pocket in brisket.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight in sauce made of Italian dressing, soy sauce, oregano, vinegar, water, and garlic salt.
Place pan containing all above in oven.
Bake covered 2 hours at 350 to 375 degrees.
Remove, uncover and cool for 30 minutes.
Open pocket and layer with mushrooms, onions, bell pepper and bacon.
Close pocket.
Sprinkle Tbsp salt and 2 tsp. black pepper on top surface of brisket.
Return to oven and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Remove from oven. Slice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar together until smooth.
Add eggs, then sift flour with soda and add to mixture. Roll into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and with a wet fork flatten.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cole slaw
directions: Blend and pour over a chopped cabbage.
Pour extra into jar and refrigerate. Use on cabbage when you need cole slaw.

title: flag cake
directions: Bake angel food cake mix according to directions in 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Let cake cool.
Cut cake in 2 pieces that are about 1 inch thick (9 x 13 x 1)	Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add condensed milk.
Add dry pudding mix. Add 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip. Line bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 pan with 1 piece of angel food cake. Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over cake.
Top with 2/3 of the strawberries and all but 50 of the blueberries.
Place 2nd piece of angel food cake on top.	Spread remaining Cool Whip on top. Place remaining strawberries & blueberries on Cool Whip to create a flag design.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses together.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg alternately with milk and beat well after each addition.
Add raisins and nuts and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: sour cream bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour one-half the batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle one-half of it over batter in pan.
Add remaining batter and top with remaining cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch glass bowl, crush graham crackers. Add butter and mix.
Make a crust.
Blend together condensed milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Then spread strawberry filling over top.
Better to sit overnight in refrigerator covered.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, carrots, pineapple, water, eggs, oil, pecans and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed until moistened. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage 'n mac dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box.
Add cottage cheese and onion.
Mix well. Cover bottom of a 10 x 6-inch baking dish with sausage. Top with dinner mixture and remaining sausage. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: carolyn's oven chicken
directions: Beat eggs and milk together in a bowl.
Season chicken pieces in salt and pepper.
Dip pieces in milk and egg mixture.
Coat with flour (you may season flour also).

title: martha washington candy
directions: Sift powdered sugar; add vanilla and margarine.
Add enough canned cream until it's sticky to handle.
Cream until it will roll into a very soft ball.
Shape into little round balls.
A cherry or a nut may be put in center.
Coconut is good mixed with the mixture.
The filling can be made into different flavors and colors.
Dip until covered into chocolate mixture made with 4 tablespoons paraffin and chocolate.
Drop on waxed paper until cooled.
Store in airtight container.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into small balls about the size of a quarter.
Freeze until firm.
Roll each ball in bread crumbs to completely cover.
Fry until golden in oil heated to 350°.
Drain on paper toweling.
Yields about 36.

title: curried chicken
directions: Melt butter and saute onion and celery until tender.
Combine flour and curry and sprinkle over onion and celery.
Add milk; stir until thick.
Add chicken, mushrooms and lemon juice.
Serve over white rice.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco and sugar.
Add salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add beaten eggs to cooled liquids. Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Stir until dissolved and add to other liquids.
Add flour, one cup at a time, and blend well. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush top with melted butter.
Fold over in half moon shape.
Place on greased pan.
Let stand 3 hours.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° until brown.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water and sugar 10 minutes in a pot.
Stir in coffee. Cool and then stir in vodka.
Cut up bean and put mixture into dark 1/2 gallon container for up to 3 weeks.

title: butterfly salad
directions: Put pineapple on lettuce leaf.
Top with cranberry slices and cottage cheese.
Serve with dressing.

title: mama-su cucumber salad
directions: Put cucumbers in bowl and sprinkle with a tablespoon of salt. Mix well and let stand about 20 minutes.
Drain and squeeze out excess liquid.

title: hershey's syrup brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add syrup and eggs, one at a time. Add flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cut beef into 5 or 6 chunks.
Place in roaster.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over beef.
Heat to boiling on top of range.
Cover and place in 300° oven for 6 hours or until meat can be shredded.

title: bonfrisco chicken
directions: For this recipe, you can use a cut up chicken, chicken breasts or whatever pieces your family likes.

title: olive cheese nuggets
directions: Blend shredded cheese with butter.
Sift the flour and paprika into cheese and butter mixture.
Mix firm dough.
Take 1 teaspoon of dough and roll into a ball.
Flatten in palm of hand.
Place 1 olive in center.
Shape dough around olive, rolling back into a ball.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Serve hot.
Yields 24 servings.

title: the best cheesecake
directions: Blend together cheesecake mix, milk, cream cheese; whip in Cool Whip.
Pour batter immediately over ladyfingers which are lined in a spring-form pan.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Apply topping just before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread and sausage in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over bread and meat.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tennessee mud pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together. Remove from heat; stir in sugar and beaten eggs. Mix well. Add flour, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla; mix well. Spoon batter into a greased 13x9x2 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on top of warm cake; cover with chocolate frosting.

title: special bran muffins(low calorie)
directions: Put grated carrots in large bowl.
Add mashed bananas and beaten egg.
Add sugar and bran.
Let stand 3 minutes.
In small bowl, mix dry ingredients and then add to bran mixture.
Add raisins and fold in oil.
Bake in nonstick muffin pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.
One muffin equals 124 calories or 1 bread, 1 fruit and 1/2 fat exchanges.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: In large percolator coffeepot, mix apple juice, cranberry juice, water and brown sugar.
In basket of the coffeepot, mix cloves, cinnamon stick pieces and salt.
Perk as you do for coffee. Nice for the holiday season!
Yields 30 to 35 servings.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars together in a large bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla, soda and salt.
Mix in flour.
Add oats, coconut, Post Toasties, pecans, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and butter brickles.
Drop mixture from tablespoon and flatten with teaspoon. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown onions and ground beef.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Place 4 tortillas in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place half of the meat over the top and then half of the cheese.
Repeat the layers. Pour 1/2 cup water around the edge and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: black beans
directions: Soak black beans in water overnight.
The water amount needs to be plentiful so that approximately 1-inch of water remains above the beans after soaking.
Add everything but lemon juice and Worcestershire.
Add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce last 1/2 hour of cooking.
Cook until beans are soft.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in large tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Line 9 inch x 13 inch pan with layer of ice cream sandwiches side to side.
Spread half of the Cool Whip, top with half of the fudge sauce.
Layer with more sandwiches, remainder of Cool Whip and remainder of hot fudge sauce.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Freeze 4 -5 hours.
Soften 15 - 20 minutes before serving.
Freeze leftovers.

title: mexican buffet
directions: Set bowls of each ingredient in order as listed.
Let each guest fix their own, buffet style.
Start at the beginning of recipe, placing one ingredient on top of the other.
Do not skip any.

title: new orleans veggie casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes as thinly as possible.
Remove seeds and cut peppers into wide strips.
Peel and thinly slice onions. Cut eggplant (with or without peel) into cubes or slices.
Saute each vegetable separately in olive oil until soft and just beginning to brown.
(Don't fry tomatoes.)
Layer vegetables in large casserole after sauteing, first potatoes, then onions, peppers and eggplant.
Season each layer with salt and red pepper. Sprinkle garlic powder lightly over all.
Cover with tomatoes. Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8. Tasty.

title: breakfast before
directions: Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Tear bread into pieces and place in dish.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread in baking dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Place sausage on top of egg mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.

title: english walnut candy
directions: Put all ingredients in a large kettle, except the walnut meats.
Cook until soft candy, stirring quite frequently.
Beat until creamy, then add walnuts.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yum!

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Place into a 6 x 4-inch glass dish.
Layer lettuce, celery and eggs (finely chopped). Season lightly.
Continue layering with peas, green pepper and onion evenly.
Season lightly.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread evenly over the top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese on top and cover with plastic wrap.
Chill for 12 hours.

title: iced tea(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Bring to boil the 3 cups of water. When it starts to boil, remove from heat and add the tea bags. Cover with lid at least 5 minutes. Add the sugar in a mixing container. Add 1 cup warm water until sugar melts, then add tea. Continue adding water over tea bags and pouring into gallon container until full. Makes the best tea. You can use less sugar if you don't want it real sweet.

title: grandma's pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Combine with dry.
Turn griddle on medium.
Heat griddle or pan until drop of water sizzles.
Drop batter by spoonfuls.
Flip when bubbles start to pop.

title: english toffee
directions: Over high flame, melt butter, sugar and water.
Boil together 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add almonds.
Cook very fast until mixture becomes caramel colored.
Pour into greased pan or shallow dish.
Break Hershey bars over surface.
When chocolate is melted, gently spread to cover top, then sprinkle with ground nuts.

title: smoked beef sausage
directions: Slice sausage in 1/4-inch slices.
Saute onion, pepper and sausage in butter.
Add sauerkraut and mustard.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve with pita bread, cut in half, or French rolls.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth (food processor works great!).
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli enough to separate pieces, then mix with uncooked rice.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Store in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is lightly brown.
Serves 20.
This freezes nicely.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Place in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix
soup
and
water (or broth). Pour over the chicken.
Mix
stuffing according to directions. Add to the chicken and soup.
Bake
to
45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Place green beans in 3-quart casserole.
Add water.
Cover with a lid.
Cook at High for 5 minutes; stir.
Cook at High for 6 to 8 minutes, or until beans are tender.
Drain.
Let stand, covered.

title: raspberry-blueberry salad
directions: 1st Layer:
One package raspberry Jell-O.
Omit 1/2 cup water.

title: family favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal,
raisins (soak raisins in hot water, then drain if you like moister raisins) and nuts. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: easy chocolate fudge cake
directions: Bake box cake in sheet pan. Just before the cake is to come out of the oven, combine the margarine, cocoa, and milk in a saucepan and bring to a rapid boil. Remove from heat and add powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts. Beat well and spread on hot cake.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water; add 2 teaspoons of sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add milk, oil, salt and remaining sugar.
Add enough flour to form a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth, about 10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl and turn over to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about 2 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down. Divide into 4 pieces; divide 1 piece into 12 balls.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place rolls on greased baking sheets.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal macaroon cookies
directions: Sift flour once, measure and sift 3 times with other dry ingredients.
Add oats.
Cream butter; add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add nuts, raisins and milk.
Add flour mixture in small amounts at a time and blend.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Soften cheese and sausage.
Mix with Bisquick. Roll in balls (about the size of a large marble).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°. Freeze.
Reheat as needed at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: szechuan chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and pepper in small bowl. Dredge chicken in cornstarch.
Heat oil in wok over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic; stir-fry until chicken is opaque, about 5 minutes.
Add soy mixture and stir-fry 30 seconds.
Mix in green onions.
Serve over rice.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Press biscuits into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef; drain and spread over biscuits.
Saute onion and spread over beef.
Drain corn and spread over onion.
Spread potatoes over corn.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook at 450° until biscuits are done and cheese melted.

title: monkey bread
directions: Can add some pecans.

title: pineapple-cream cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and heat.
Pour over jello to dissolve and cool.
Add pineapple.
Beat cream and cheese together and add rest of ingredients.
Put into mold and chill.
Serves 12.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Thaw loaves at room temperature for 3 1/2 hours (do not let rise).
Break or cut off into chunks the size of ping-pong balls and put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and pour rest of ingredients over bread dough, cover loosely with foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 20 to 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes, then turn out onto waxed paper.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together dry ingredients. Combine in a bowl the butter, oatmeal, sweetener, egg, milk and then dry ingredients. Add raisins and nuts.
Mix dough well and drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, pepper, celery, eggs, peas, bacon and cheese in that order.
Spread mayonnaise over salad.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: lazy stroganoff
directions: No need to brown meat. Simply mix all together and bake in covered dish at 275° for 3 to 4 hours. Or cook in crock-pot for 4 hours. The flavor depends on slow cooking. Ten minutes before serving, stir in 1 cup sour cream. Serve over rice.

title: pilgrim bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, brown sugar and salt in a bowl.
Stir in gradually 2 cups boiling water; add oil.
Cool to lukewarm. Combine flours in a bowl.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Combine cornmeal, flour and yeast mixtures.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Punch dough down.
Divide in half and knead 3 minutes.
Shape into 2 greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Put into a baking dish.
Crumble bacon on top of ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold after being baked first.

title: oatmeal and raisin cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.

title: the stuff
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together. Spread into greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dr. hawley's lemon bread
directions: Cream sugar with margarine.
Add lemon rind.
Beat in eggs. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in nuts. Pour in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 90 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Heat sugar in lemon juice, stirring until dissolved.
Pour over hot bread; cool in pan.
Remove when cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well; refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: apple butter in a crock-pot
directions: Prepare apples as for applesauce.
Puree fruit using blender or food strainer.
Pour into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on high for 8 to 10 hours.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Remove cover during last half hour of cooking.
Jar immediately in hot jars and seal.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Arrange strawberries in the bottom of pie shell.
Mix cornstarch and 1 1/2 cups water in saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes. Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool slightly; pour over strawberries and chill until set.
Serve with whipped topping or plain.

title: snickerdoodle snack
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Cream together the oleo, sugar and eggs.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Roll into balls, then roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes. Stir in nuts.
Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Pour mix over crackers.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cut while still warm.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in a dry place.
Use 1/2 cup mix and fill with hot water.

title: rinschler's special soap
directions: Clarify fat by cooking up in water and let harden.
Scrape off dirt from the bottom.
Do this until clean.
Bring water to a boil.
Dissolve Borax in water; add almond oil and lye and let cool, then add ammonia.
Heat fat hot; add to cold lye mixture. Stir well.

title: fresh frozen coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, using margarine instead of butter.
Make two layers.
When cake is completely cooled, split into four layers.
(Pulling a piece of thread through layer splits it nicely.)
Mix sour cream and sugar, then add coconut. Save about 2 tablespoons to sprinkle on top of cake.
Spread the filling between all the layers.
Frost with Cool Whip on sides and top.
Sprinkle reserved coconut on top.
Cover and place in refrigerator for two days before serving.
Enjoy!

title: collard greens
directions: Wash ham hock and place in a pot with cold water to cover. Add pepper flakes; cover with lid and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour; add more water if necessary. Wash greens and rinse well.
When the hock is done, add the greens and remaining ingredients to the pot.
Lower heat and simmer until tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir.
Season to taste and serve with extra vinegar and hot sauce on the side.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Adding milk until the mixture reaches the desired texture you want. Mix by hand or with an electric mixer until creamy. Ice cake of your choice.

title: manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown meat and drain.
Soak torn bread pieces in milk.
Add cheeses and egg; mix together.
Add cheese and bread mixture to meat.	Stuff in noodles.
Pour 1/2 of sauce in the bottom of a baking dish.
Put stuffed noodles in dish. Pour
other
of sauce over noodles.
Bake, covered, for
1 hour
or
until noodles are soft.
Sprinkle more Mozzarella cheese on top when ready to serve.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the cheese and butter. Add other ingredients.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: french raisin cookies
directions: Wash and soak raisins in hot water.
Drain and dry on paper towel.
Put all ingredients in bowl; stir well.
Bake on large cookie sheet at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Ice while hot with powdered sugar and water and a drop of vanilla flavoring.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Layer green beans, corn, almonds, sour cream, onion and celery.
Pam dish.
End with Ritz crackers on top.
Pour melted butter over crackers and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, combine macaroni, hamburger and sauce. Layer the top with pepperoni. Top with cheese. Bake 1/2 hour at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: beef roast
directions: Line pan with foil.
Sprinkle roast with the onion soup mix. Cover with other soups.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours or until tender.

title: whip cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating real good after each egg. Add flour and cream, alternating, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla. Pour into a well-greased tube pan. Place in a cold oven. Set oven at 300° for 30 minutes. Then turn to 325° for 45 minutes. Do not open oven during cooking. Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: ellen's surprise
directions: Make pudding using buttermilk; add Cool Whip and fruit.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well.
Form in loaf.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: artichoke bites
directions: Place bread onto cookie sheet.
Brush each little bread slice with melted butter.
Open artichokes and drain.
Cut each artichoke into sixths.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
(For fried rice, rice does better in rice cooker.
When bell goes off, turn off and uncover.)
Heat wok over stove until hot.
Add oil and let oil get hot.
Add eggs and stir continuously until eggs are just done (very fluffy).
Remove eggs.
If more oil is needed, add about 1/4 cup.
Add garlic and onion; stir-fry until tender.
Add pork and stir-fry until cooked. Add shrimp and cook until tender.
Add mushrooms and vegetables and stir-fry until tender.
Add cooked eggs, soy sauce, accent, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Turn fire low and mix in cooked rice. Before serving, sprinkle green onions over rice for garnish (optional)!

title: cheddar cheese grits souffle
directions: Cook grits as directed on package.
Remove from heat and beat in 2 eggs, one at a time.
Stir in 2 cups Cheddar cheese (8 ounces).
Season with a few drops of Tabasco.

title: drop banana cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, and bananas. Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Add to banana mixture slowly while mixing.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together bread crumbs, dash of garlic, eggs, salt and pepper to taste, chopped onion, ground meat, sauce and cheese. Add milk, just enough to soften. Form into balls.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Put in crock-pot. Do not put any grease in.

title: mushroom smothered steak
directions: Cut steak into strips and marinate in beer for 2 hours.
Cut onions into onion rings and saute in butter.
Lay steak strips in casserole dish and pour onion rings on top steak strips.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over steak and onions.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Use glass pie pan. Put cream cheese on bottom; top with chopped onions, can of chili and Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve with nacho chips.

title: curried chicken(old recipe made easy)
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 3 hours at 275°.

title: coconut layer cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time; beating well.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add extract.

Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and baking powder; add gradually, reserving enough to dredge nuts and raisins, then fold them into the cake mixture. Pour into large angel cake pan, completely lined with brown paper, not greased.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in oil.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder, then add tomatoes, tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Cook on low heat, keep stirring occasionally.
A dash of Worcestershire sauce may be used if desired.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Cook
pasta
in boiling water per package instructions. Preheat oven
to
Saute
ground
chuck, onion and green pepper in
skillet until brown.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, bay leaf, oregano
and	thyme.	Simmer	for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of cheese.
Stir until melted.	Fold cooked pasta into sauce. Grease
baking
dish.
Pour pasta and sauce into dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: grandma tovern's brunswick stew
directions: Simmer beef and pork in water until tender.
Grind or chop fine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add broth as needed for juiciness. Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon swirl loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water. Heat milk, 1/4 cup of the sugar, margarine and salt to 110°.
Add to the yeast mixture with 1 1/2 cups of the flour, egg and raisins.
Beat for 3 minutes. Stir in 1 cup more flour.
Turn out on floured surface; knead for 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough. Roll out to 9 x 18-inch rectangle.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough. Starting at narrow end, tightly roll up.
Place in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pedialyte
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until marshmallows dissolve.
Place in refrigerator to thicken.
Remove and whip with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Return to refrigerator until firm.

title: ginger zing salad
directions: To section the orange easily, cut a slice off the top and bottom and stand on a cutting board.
Starting at the top end, cut off peel, exposing the orange segments.
Continue until orange is completely peeled.	Then holding orange in your hand, cut out segments from between the membranes.
Work over a large bowl to catch any juice.
Add grapes and strawberries.
Peel and slice bananas.
Combine well with other fruit.
Whisk marmalade with honey and juice.
Stir in the ginger.
Combine dressing with fruit and let marinate for at least 30 minutes.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: trifle
directions: Choose yogurt and fresh fruit to complement each other.
I use strawberry, blueberry and raspberry most often.

title: romanian egg dumplings
directions: Mix together
and
drop
into
chicken soup by the teaspoon. Cook
minutes
with lid on and 10 minutes with lid off. Depending
on
the
size of your family, you may want to make 1 or 2 more batches.
This is a very moist dumpling.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Boil eggplant in salted boiling water just until tender.
Drain well.
Mix together tomato sauce with seasoning.
Alternate sauce with eggplant.
Top with remaining sauce, Monterey Jack cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Mix together bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: black forest pie
directions: Add pudding to pie crust for layering.
Add Cool Whip on top, leaving a center for cherries.
Add cherries.

title: pumpkin chip muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl beat eggs pumpkin and butter.
Stir into dry ingredients just until blended, fold in chips.
Greased or paper-lined muffin cups, bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add as listed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy butterscotch chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set.
Let stand for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: butterscotch icebox cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Mix well; add nuts.
Will be a stiff batter.
Chill in refrigerator for awhile or overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter and eggs.
Then add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and add to mixture a little at a time.
Mix well. Roll on floured board and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 70 cookies.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups sugar, oil, buttermilk, flour, salt, baking powder, soda and eggs.
Pour into 3 cake pans and bake at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the melted butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 cups flour well. Press into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 15 to 25 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; cool.
Mix mayonnaise and milk.
Add to Jell-O.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix and store in glass jar.
For 1 cup tea, mix 1 teaspoon mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: western beans
directions: Drain liquid from all beans. Mix all ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: skinny french fries(low-fat recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes and place in bowl of ice water to keep crisp.
Drain and pat dry.
Combine potatoes with oil in bowl and mix with hands to distribute oil evenly over potatoes.
Spread on a baking sheet and bake until golden brown and tender, about 30 t0 40 minutes, turning frequently.
Sprinkle with paprika and salt.
Serves 4.
Calories per serving:
130. Fat per serving: 2.3 g.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk in bowl.
Mix in peanut butter; lightly whip the Cool Whip in with the pudding and peanut butter. Mix by hand.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until firm.
Garnish with chopped peanuts.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients in saucepan until cheese is completed melted.
Add shrimp, crab, clams, etc.
Cook the linguine noodles; drain.
Serve sauce over linguine.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Alternate flour and milk.
Add flavoring.
Fold in pecans and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool.

title: my brownies
directions: In large bowl, mix cocoa and oil.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well; gradually add flour and mix well.
Bake at 350° in square pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Fill a well-oiled baking dish with alternate layers of asparagus, cheese, white sauce and sliced eggs. Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper. Bake in moderate oven (400°) about 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: zack's sport pita
directions: Put several slices of your favorite cheese inside pita bread. Microwave for 1 minute and cut in 4 sections and serve.
Be creative and add optional ingredients when feeling adventurous.

title: chocolate-raspberry cheesecake
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth. Add egg, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well. Arrange raspberries on bottom of crust and slowly pour cheese mixture over the fruit. Bake 30-35 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add nuts.
Mix well. Flatten 1 teaspoon dough and put a date half in middle.
Pinch dough around date half and roll into a ball.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.
These freeze well on a cookie sheet, then store in plastic bag.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Crumble sausage and onion and brown in skillet.
Add scrambled raw eggs and cook until desired consistency.
Spoon egg mixture into tortilla and add cheese and salsa to taste.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Toss apples
with brown sugar and allspice in a medium-size bowl.
Spread
tablespoons
apple mixture over half of each pastry round; fold other half evenly over filling.	Press around edges with fork to seal.
Pour enough oil into deep fat fryer or skillet to make 1 inch;
heat to 350°.
Fry turnovers in hot oil, turning often, for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden; drain well
on paper
towel.
While still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve slightly warm.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll out in small biscuits.
Bake at 15 minutes at 450°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes approximately 1/4-inch thick and place in large saucepan with olive oil spread on bottom of pan.
Add onion, salt, pepper, dill and ketchup.
Cover saucepan and put on low heat. Stir occasionally to mix tomatoes.
Slice ring bologna into 1/4-inch slices and add to tomatoes after 15 minutes.
Simmer meat and tomatoes until tomatoes are fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
This should take approximately 25 minutes.
Serve in small soup bowls.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cup
directions: Combine at least five or more fruits (use any fruits desired).
Stir fruit and then add applesauce to desired consistency.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture clings, then press in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Beat together eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Sift together 1/4 cup flour and baking powder; stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust, then bake again for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Refrigerate, then cut.

title: fruit and spinach salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving 1 tablespoon of the liquid. In a large bowl, combine fruit cocktail, torn spinach and raisins. Toss gently to mix.

title: borscht(beet soup)
directions: Heat oil in 5-quart pan.
Dice onions and carrots.
Cook until soft (about 10 minutes).
Add the broth.
Finely chop or grate beets in food processor.
Chop the leafy tops also, adding both to soup.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Cover and simmer over low heat until all vegetables are tender (about 45 minutes).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish each bowlful with a generous spoonful of sour cream.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease and add beef gravy. Prepare mashed potatoes.
In pie shell or casserole dish, spoon in drained can of corn.
Cover with beef and gravy mixture.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Heat in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until potatoes are slightly browned.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminum.
Wash and drain 3 times in clear water.
Soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a low boil; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumbers and soak 5 or 6 hours or overnight.
Boil cucumbers in soaking solution for 35 minutes. Fill sterilized quart jars with cucumber slices and fill with liquid to 1/2-inch of jar top.
Put lids on tight and put in a boiling water bath for 5 minutes, full boil.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions until well mixed.
Cover, chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Cut top from round bread and remove inside soft bread making a bowl.
After stirring dip to mix well, spoon into bread bowl and replace lid on top of bread.
Toast bread leftovers and serve with dip along with salad crackers.

title: flowerpot cake or dirt cake
directions: Mix together well the vanilla pudding, milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Alternate layers, starting with cookies and ending with cookies.
Add flower and spade.

title: mock white castle(serves 24)
directions: Mix together.
Cook on large flat cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Section off to equal 24.
Put on bun; add dill pickle on top.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Combine butter, sugar and buttermilk in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir only until flour is well moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Fill paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Drain beans.
Mix brown sugar and dry mustard.
Pour over beans and toss gently to coat.
Divide beans into bundles and wrap with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Place seam side down in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus-english pea casserole
directions: Mix asparagus, peas and pimento.
Mix reserved juice of asparagus with a little cream soup.
Pour over top.
Grate cheese over top of the above.
Mix mushroom and celery soups and spread over the first 5 ingredients (asparagus, peas, pimiento, juice-soup and cheese).
Mix some bread crumbs, crushed potato chips and crushed Ritz crackers; sprinkle over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pixie cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add chocolate.
Heat together, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Let cool slightly.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except confectioners sugar (batter will be stiff).
Blend well.
Place in refrigerator and chill at least 30 minutes.

title: fried zucchini cakes
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a frypan.
Spoon batter (2 heaping tablespoonfuls makes a nice size) into skillet.
Flatten with spatula.
Cook over medium heat until browned on both sides. Serve plain or top with tomato sauce and grated cheese or sour cream and chives.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown in a 350° oven.

title: corned beef and cabbage, irish style
directions: Mix all ingredients well; refrigerate.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown ground beef and add onion and bell pepper.
Bring 3 quarts of water to a boil.
Add ingredients except rice.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add instant rice and cook 5 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sour milk donuts
directions: Knead; roll out and cut.
Fry in deep fat.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring water and spices to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover and steep for 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add sugar.
Stir just until sugar dissolves.
Add juices and a few drops of food coloring.
Serve hot.

title: baked onions in wine mushroom sauce
directions: In a heavy frying pan, saute onion until soft in olive oil. Add garlic and saute a few more minutes.
Add spices and chili pepper.
Add beans.
Mash with potato masher or the back of a wooden spoon until desired consistency is reached.
May be pureed in a blender if desired.

title: hungry boy casserole
directions: Mix browned ground beef, celery, onion and peppers and drain. Add tomato paste, water and seasoning.
Mix well and take out one cup mixture for biscuit roll-ups.
Add beans; simmer while preparing Biscuit Mix.

title: loaded mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until tender.
Drain and place in a mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat on medium-low speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in 2 cups cheese, bacon and onions.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour all ingredients in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: milk punch
directions: Very pretty and good.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into balls the size of a large marble. Dip into dipping chocolate. Let dry on wax paper. Store in an air tight container.

title: spinach tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
Fry bacon and crumble.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line greased pan with crescent rolls. Sprinkle 1 pound cooked sausage in casserole pan. Add milk and eggs.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cappuccino
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in jar or other container with lid.
Mix 3 tablespoons of mix in cup of boiling water.

title: easy oatmeal cookies (squares)
directions: Melt margarine and syrup over low heat, when melted add baking soda and allow to cool a bit.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits; flatten into 5-inch circles. Grease muffin pan and press each biscuit into the bottom and sides of each muffin cup; set aside.

title: puu puu cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in medium fryer until crisp.
Remove most of drippings, leaving enough to coat pan.
Drain bacon.
Chop cabbage and onion and place in pan with drippings.
Cover and cook over medium heat until tender.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over vegetables.
Mix vinegar and bacon drippings and pour over vegetables.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning.
Cover bottom of baking dish with refried beans.
Layer hamburg mix on top of beans.
Cover with cheese sauce or soup, olives and then shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: cinnamon pound cake(a no-fail pound cake that everyone loves)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating well.
Grease Bundt cake pan.
Dust pan with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Pour batter into pan in thirds, sprinkling each layer with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: *Sour milk:
Add one tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar to one cup milk.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Roll out; cut and place on a well buttered pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: tried and true meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add eggs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add meat and mix.
Shape into a loaf and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
The last 30 minutes I like to spread catsup over the top with pastry brush.

title: sesame chicken appetizer
directions: Mix first three ingredients and set aside.
Mix crumbs and sesame seeds.
Coat chicken with mayonnaise mixture, and then crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet and bake in 425° oven 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot with dip.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix well; form into a ball or brick.
Chill.
When ready to serve, pour a bit of the seafood sauce over the cheese mixture. Scoop with crackers and enjoy.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl in order given.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Flatten with fork or hand. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Check after 10 minutes.
Bake until golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Layer cracker crumbs, cheese, asparagus and liquid.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with a few crumbs and a little cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Bring
to
boiling point.
Stir for about 20 minutes or until thickness desired.

title: party meat balls
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape firmly into 48 (1/2 inch) meat balls. Arrange in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until meatballs are no longer pink.

title: ham delights
directions: Completely slice through the middle of rolls, horizontally. Separate into two layers.
Cream margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire, mustard, and onion.
Spread on inside of top and bottom of bread.
Layer ham and cheese between 2 layers of bread. Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately, cut into individual rolls.	Yields:
60 rolls.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Start out on low heat about 3 minutes, then up on high.
Boil together five minutes the rhubarb and sugar, while hot stir in the jello and add drop of food coloring.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in corn meal. Add eggs, milk and shortening. Beat until smooth but do not over-beat. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 425 for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage boats
directions: Cook whole, unpeeled zucchini in boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Cut in half lengthwise; drain.
Scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch thick walls.
Chop centers.
Brown sausage and onion.
Pour off fat.
Stir in chopped zucchini, bread crumbs, catsup, egg, salt and thyme.
Place zucchini shells in large, shallow baking dish and fill with sausage mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill-icious tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, mayonnaise, celery, green onions and dill weed. Stir in oats.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix butter and crushed graham crackers.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Place over top of graham cracker mixture.
Place pie filling over.
Chill.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Lay out cream cheese for 1 hour at room temperature.
Grate corned beef or ham in food processor.
Sprinkle corned beef on some foil and a little on side.
Put the rest in with cream cheese.
Grate all onions up; mix with cream cheese and corned beef mix.
Blend with mixer.
Form balls; roll in corned beef or ham.
Chill.

title: spiced tea
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young, and take only such as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere. Some wives insist on keeping husbands in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses.
Keep them warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with three good meals a day. When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: chocolate walnut pie
directions: Cream together the eggs, salt, vanilla, corn syrup and sugar. Blend in chocolate bits and walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat, at medium speed, until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: black cookies
directions: Turn the toaster on.
Put the cookies in the toaster for 100 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth and creamy.
Very good on any fruit.

title: rose bud punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding the powdered sugar and grenadine last.

title: frankfurter relish
directions: Grind onions and peppers and drain.
Add sugar, vinegar, flour and turmeric and bring to a boil.
Add a small jar of mustard. Makes 4 1/2 quarts.
Put at once into clean, hot sterile jars; seal.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and press down.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit mousse for diabetics
directions: Mix cold water	and milk.
Beat until stiff.
Add fruit juice and sweetener.
Pour into freezing tray and freeze until creamy firm.
Makes
servings	of 1/2 cup each.
(Calories per serving:

title: grilled pork chops
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first six ingredients.
Set aside 1/3 cup for basting; add pork chops to the remaining marinade.
Seal and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Drain and discard marinade.
Grill chops, covered, over medium-hot heat for 4 minutes.
Turn; baste with reserved marinade. Grill 4 to 7 minutes longer or until juices run clear. Yield: 6 servings.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini according to package.
Drain and add all other ingredients.
Chill for several hours.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix.
Lightly butter pan (13 x 9-inch).
Spread mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, tartar, soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly brown but still soft. These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grand executive inn goober pea salad
directions: Put peas in large bowl to thaw, then add rest of ingredients. If making ahead of time, add peanuts just before serving.

title: easy refried beans
directions: Sort through and discard any foreign material.
Thoroughly wash and drain beans.
Combine beans, water, 1/3 cup of picante sauce, onion, salt and garlic in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover; simmer 3 to 4 hours or until beans are tender and mash easily.
Stir occasionally.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Return beans to Dutch oven or large mixing bowl.
Add butter and remaining picante sauce.
Beat at low speed with mixer, adding liquid as necessary, until desired consistency.

title: rhubarb spread(heritage recipe)
directions: Boil 10 minutes.
Add 1 pkg. strawberry Jello.
Seal while hot.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk until creamy.
Then add sour cream and Cool Whip until smooth.
Layer pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of hot water.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water.
Cut cheese in cubes and add to grits.
Stir until melted.
Add oleo, seasoned salt, corn and onion.
Bake for 1 hour in greased casserole at 350°.
May be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen, either cooked or uncooked.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients with mixer at medium speed. Beat in milk gradually.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking dish. Bake at 375° about 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Top with marshmallows and return to oven for about 12 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed and browned.
Serves 6.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cover chicken with remaining ingredients.
Let marinate overnight.
The longer the better.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover if they begin to brown too fast.

title: toasty cheese dip
directions: Set aside bread hollowed out of loaf.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Spoon into hollowed out bread loaf.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Dice the hollowed out bread that was set aside and serve with the baked loaf.
(May need to dice extra bread.)

title: pistachio fruit dip
directions: Mix package of pudding with 1/2 cup of water; whisk vigorously, then add Amaretto and then Cool Whip.
Use this dip with fresh cut-up fruit.

title: delicious oven baked chicken
directions: Soak fryers in brine of Tender Quick or salt and water overnight.
Drain; dip in vegetable oil, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Put foil on cookie sheets first.
Bake chicken at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not salt before baking.
Very good.

title: tomato bacon cups
directions: Separate each biscuit into three layers, put each layer into mini cupcake pan. Mix remaining ingredients; spoon mixture into biscuit. Bake at 375° for 10 - 15 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: 7 layered salad
directions: Cut or tear 1 fresh head lettuce.
Sprinkle with onion.
Add crisp bacon (or Bac*Os).
Next, add a layer of finely chopped cauliflower.
Add frozen peas.
Mix salad dressing with sugar. Spread over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Best when refrigerated overnight!

title: baked halibut with sour cream and cheese
directions: Place halibut in a well buttered baking dish.
Combine all ingredients except cheese, and pour over the halibut.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and broil just long enough to brown the cheese lightly.

title: tuna logs
directions: Mix all together and roll into 2 logs.
Roll 1 log in parsley flakes and the other in paprika.
Chill.
Slice and serve on Ritz crackers.
Very nice at Christmas time.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer 8 slices of bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sausage and
cheese over.
Add rest of bread.
Mix eggs, mustard and milk.
Pour mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt
margarine
and Crisco;
add remaining ingredients in order. Mix with spoon.
Chill mixture 30 minutes.
Drop and bake at 350°.

title: pull taffy
directions: Boil butter, brown sugar and Karo syrup until crackle stage. Add vanilla when done.
Pour into cookie sheet until cool, then pull until pearly.

title: london broil
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and 1/4 teaspoon salt; cook and stir until onions are tender.
Keep warm over low heat.

title: sweet potato angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add the yeast and water.
Mix in warm mashed sweet potatoes, adding enough to make a smooth dough.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat.
In a small roaster or casserole, layer as follows:
meat, onions, Creamettes and celery.
Add water if dish appears dry.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: lovely cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese well; add eggs and sugar, mixing well, scraping bowl.
Add vanilla and cream, beating about 15 minutes (the longer the mixing the higher the cake).
Add mixture to graham cracker crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Then leave in oven for 1 hour more with heat off (put pan of water in oven with cake).

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and whipped cream cheese.
Spread on large flat dish, like a meat platter, then add other ingredients in order given, sprinkling Mozzarella cheese over the top.
Serve with corn chips.
Enjoy!!

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; stir well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares or bars.
Makes 20.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put in shallow casserole and top with cracker crumbs. Moisten with butter and Bake.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread on cake while hot.

title: coconut swirls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add the sugar and dry milk.
Add coconut.
Drop on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Top with melted chocolate.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple pie topping
directions: Cook margarine, brown sugar and Pet milk until it comes to
a boil.
Add	pecans and spread on pie.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Clean onions, cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate rings. Combine slightly beaten egg yolk and mix in flour, salt and one teaspoon melted Crisco until smooth.
Dip onion rings in batter. Fry in 3/4-inch Crisco, heated to 365°, in a skillet.
Cook until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Mix all together and heat until cheese melts.
Easy and very good.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and garlic in butter.
Add seasonings, olives and tomato sauce.
In a round 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of buttered tortillas, meat sauce and cheese, ending with tortillas and cheese.
Pour water down side of casserole dish, cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 8.

title: brownie cake and ice cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
With wax paper, line the bottom of a 13 X 9 baking pan.
Beat the eggs in a large bowl at high speed for 2 minutes.
Reserve 1 Cup dry brownie mix an the chocolate flavor packet for the chocolate sauce.
Combine the remaining mix and baking powder; add to the beaten eggs.
Blend at lowest speed just until mixed, batter will be thin.
Pour in to the wax lined pan. Bake at 375 for 12-15 minutes. test with toothpick for doneness. Immediately after baking cut around the sides and turn out on a cloth covered with confectioners sugar.
Remove the wax paper and roll cake and cloth together, start with the long side.
Cool completely.

title: creamy broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add onion; saute briefly (do not brown).
Add flour and stir quickly to thoroughly combine.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk, stirring until thoroughly blended. Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add cheese and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thick and creamy, about 2 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler.
Blend in milk gradually.
Cook over boiling water, stirring occasionally until thickened, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Stir a small amount of hot cornstarch mixture into the beaten eggs, then stir the eggs into the remaining cornstarch mixture.
Cook over boiling water 4 to 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Chill thoroughly (this is essential for a smooth cream).
Stir in vanilla and chilled cream.
Fill a 1-gallon freezer container not more than 2/3 full. Freeze in a hand-cranked or electric freezer with a mixture of 1 part ice cream salt and 6 parts crushed ice.

title: peppermint stick pie
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk in double boiler until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, salt, extract and color.
Put on ice until chilled.
Beat heavy cream until stiff.
Mix into cooled marshmallow mixture.
Pour into Oreo crust.
Put in freezer.
Thaw before eating.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pretzel salad dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar together.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Let cool.

title: grandma sherrard's porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, form into 1-inch balls.
Mix soup and water; heat to boil.
Drop meat balls into soup mixture and cover tightly.
Cook for 40 minutes (simmer).

title: liz's fudge
directions: Mix the sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil 6 full minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in large pan and let cool. Cut in squares.
Yields approximately 5 pounds.

title: asparagus ham rolls
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and cook until thick.
Gradually stir in milk and cook until bubbly and thickened. Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Place three asparagus stalks on each ham slice.
Roll up; fasten with toothpicks, if necessary.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Add pickling lime to water.
Slice cucumbers.
Put in lime water.
Soak overnight or 12 hours in crockery on enamelware.
Add sugar, vinegar and pickle mix in large pan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over packed pickles in jars.
Cap each jar when filled.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Cook bacon and set aside for later.
Cook ground beef and onion in bacon drippings.
This is when I like to add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Depending on your taste, you could add Worcestershire sauce, chili powder or even Tabasco sauce.
When beef is browned, add potatoes and tomatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft, but not mushy, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Add corn and beans and simmer until they are hot.
Crumble bacon in a separate bowl.
Serve in bowls topped with crumbled bacon.* Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix eggs, cake mix and pudding together.
Put into a greased cookie sheet with sides.
Top mixture with the chocolate chips, sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done (about 20 to 25 minutes).

title: chicken-fried round steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into 6 pieces.
Blend egg and milk.
Combine cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Slowly brown meat in hot oil. Cover tightly and cook over low heat until the meat is tender, approximately 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Pour cake mix over pumpkin mix as evenly as possible.
Pat in pecans.
Pour margarine over.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Turn pan upside down and dump cake on cookie sheet.
Cool and frost:

title: no bake chocolate nut cookies
directions: In bowl, combine oats, cocoa, nuts and coconut in pan.
Put sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil, stirring to combine. Pour over oats mixture.
Mix lightly until blended.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Melt sugar, milk and butter together until liquid.
Drop biscuits in mixture just enough to coat biscuits.
Drop in an angel food pan.
If any mixture is left, pour in pan also.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients by hand. Add flour and baking powder. Bring margarine and milk to boil to melt margarine.
Add.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Spread peanut butter over hot cake.
When cooled, melt Hershey bar and pour over peanut butter.

title: lite quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs and milk and set aside.
