Cook broccoli with 1/8 teaspoon salt until tender; discard stalks.
Cut into flowerets.
Alternate broccoli and cheese in pie crust.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in a skillet with a lid.
When you turn to brown on the second side, add chopped onions.
When the pork chops are brown, sprinkle rice over them; add salt and pepper.
Pour the tomatoes on top with pepper rings.
Cover and cook in 400° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until rice is done.
Steak or hamburger can be substituted for pork chops.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix cherry jello with boiling water.
Add miniature marshmallows; stir until melted, then add cold water.
Add drained fruit cocktail, peaches, bananas and nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and pour off grease.
Add garlic, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, Parmesan, Ricotta, parsley, egg, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles and drain.
In bottom of 9 x 13 pan, put 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture, Mozzarella slices, then 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: david's delight
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed (electric mixer) until creamy.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Combine flour mixture into creamed mixture. Blend well and by hand stir in the chocolate chips, mini M&M's and sunflower seeds (which are mixed together before dropping in the mixture).
Drop round teaspoons of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes before placing in cookie jar.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: popovers
directions: Mix together egg, milk and oil. Add flour and salt. Beat until smooth. Pour into cupcake pans, well greased and 1/2 full. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: jerry's salsa dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Melt cheese and add picante sauce to sausage.
Simmer all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: fat free deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs until hard boiled stage, cool, peel and cut in half.
Discard the yolk.
Mash the potatoes and season with salt, pepper, mustard and sweet pickle relish.
Fill eggs with the potato mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: marinated corn salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all vegetables together.
In saucepan, mix together vinegar, oil, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cool. Pour over vegetable mixture and marinate for 24 hours.
Pour off liquid and serve.
Serves 10.

title: shay's cheese casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl mix all ingredients well.
Place in a 13 x 9 inch
greased baking dish.
bake at 350° for approximately 35 or 40 minutes.
Yield:
12 - 15 servings.

title: chicken ala ellen
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Prepare stuffing according to box.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil, place in a 350 oven and bake for 45 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: western ranch dinner
directions: Heat oven to 425°.

Dip cut up chicken in 1/2 cup undiluted milk. Roll in mixture of 1 cup Bisquick, salt, pepper and paprika. Melt the shortening in a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan in the oven. Add chicken, skin side down, and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After 15 minutes, remove from pan and cool completely on rack.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to instructions on the box.
Pour 1/2 the batter into 9 x 13-inch pan that is greased and floured. Sprinkle 1/2 the sugar-butter-spice-nut-flour mixture over the batter.
Pour the balance of cake batter over the top, with balance of sugar mix sprinkled over all.
Bake according to cake instructions on box.
Cool slightly, then remove from pan. Sprinkle powdered sugar over warm cake.

title: frozen corn
directions: Fill a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan with fresh sweet corn cut from cob.
Melt margarine and pour it over the corn.
Pour the half and half or milk over it and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Bag, seal and cool corn and then put in freezer.

title: cooked cranberry sauce
directions: Cook until berries burst.
While still hot, add raspberry Jell-O.
Drain 1 can crushed pineapple; add to cranberry mixture. Refrigerate.
Better after 24 hours.

title: red chicken stew
directions: Fry streak of lean; drain and set aside. In drippings, saute onions and potatoes until slightly done. Drain off drippings and add tomato soup with 2 cans of water to dilute each can. Add mushroom soup, vinegar, 57 sauce, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper. Return meat to stew and let simmer, stirring occasionally. Add chicken pieces and let cook about 1 hour over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Serve over cooked rice. Serves approximately 20 people.

title: au gratin chicken bake
directions: Combine chicken, soup, water, chestnuts, spaghetti, 1/2 cup Cheddar, 1/2 c. Parmesan cheese, milk and pimento.
Mix and place in casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheeses and bake longer until melted.

title: rosemary - roasted potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium bowl, toss well.
Arrange on baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 450 degrees for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
In a large bowl, mix celery, onion, broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soups. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and bake for another 5 minutes.

title: macaroni-beef skillet supper
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is not pink.
Drain and rinse. Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce, catsup, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and Italian seasoning.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes. Mix in cooked macaroni.
Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: cookies from any cake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients (add nuts, coconut, etc, if you like). Bake in ungreased sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In one pot, you cook the rice.
Whenever it is a little fried, you put the tomatoes, garlic, onion and salt in.
Mix it up in a mixer.
You have to add 3 cups of water and cover it up.
Leave it to cook with a little bit of fire until it becomes dry.
You can serve it with any kind of meat.

title: microwave hardtack candy
directions: Stir syrup and sugar together in microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 9 to 12 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add flavoring and food coloring.
Pour in buttered pan.
Let set.
Cool.
Crack.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Place over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add fruit juices and bananas, mixing well. Cool.
Freeze until firm.

title: chicken divine(for chicken and dressing lovers)
directions: Boil chicken until tender, cube it, then layer this in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.

title: party punch
directions: Combine in large punch bowl and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese and salt in bowl.
Stir in milk and potatoes gradually.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: b. l. t. bites
directions: Slice top of tomatoes off and throw away.
Spoon out insides and drain on paper towel.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
When tomatoes have drained good, spoon mixture into tomatoes.
Chill for several hours, then serve.

title: italian chicken
directions: Clean chicken and place in large Ziploc freezer bag.
Pour in Italian salad dressing and close bag.
Marinate in fridge overnight, turning bag occasionally.
Next day, grill and sprinkle with lemon pepper.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie shells and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey-vegetable medley
directions: Spray a large pan with Pam.
Cook turkey until broken apart and browned.
Add all other ingredients, including some fluid from the canned vegetables to make a sauce.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, pudding, cake mix and milk with beater for 5 minutes.
Fold in chips with grated chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in boiling water until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle top with paprika for color.	Bake uncovered at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour and butter very well. Beat egg and add to flour mixture, stirring well. Add enough milk to make soft dough. Knead well. Set aside for 10 to 15 minutes.
When ready to fry, get small amounts of dough. Roll out on floured surface until thin.
Place in hot skillet with 1 1/2 to 2-inches of grease. Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and pour in buttered dish. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: never fail corn muffins
directions: Mix
as
directed.
Cook
as
directed.
Place a little butter on top of each muffin.
Serve to all that join you for dinner. Serve hot.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Mix water, salt and cheese.
Add egg yolks that have been well beaten.
Into this mixture, cut and fold stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into buttered dish and cook 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Dip slices of banana into pineapple juice.
Alternate chunks of pineapple with slices of bananas and strawberries on 5 or 7-inch skewers.
Place a cherry at the end of each skewers.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and meal.
Add butter and eggs.
Mix well. Add milk and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 30 minutes.
When pie begins to brown, cover with foil to prevent burning.

title: betty's blue ribbon barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter; fry onion until soft.
Add rest of ingredients. Cook over low heat for an hour.
If sauce becomes thick, add a little water.
I usually use 4 times the recipe to make a quart of sauce.
Put in 2 pint jars.
You can freeze if you like.
Also, I make it in microwave.
After butter, I usually microwave one minute for each 2 ingredients, then for 5 minutes when all ingredients are added.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix and store in a screw top jar. Use the amount desired in a cup of hot water, usually about 1 teaspoon per cup.

title: toni's mexican salad
directions: Spread bean dip on bottom of a platter.
Mix all balance of ingredients.
Spread on top of bean dip.
Cover with grated cheese.
Serve with taco chips for dipping.

title: spiced peanuts
directions: Boil the sugar, water and spices until syrup threads form from spoon (293° on candy thermometer).
Drop peanuts into syrup; stir until nuts are dry looking.
Pour out onto waxed paper; let stand until cold and dry.
Remove from paper and separate clumps, if needed.
Store in covered container in cool, dry spot until needed.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Blend margarine with white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water. Beat in egg. Add flour, baking soda, salt and nuts. Spread in 13 x 9 x 2 pan; sprinkle with chocolate chips. Place in 375° oven for 1 minute.
Remove and run knife through, to marbleize. Return to oven and bake 12 to 14 minutes.

title: fettuccini primavera
directions: Cook fettuccini according to package directions in skillet or wok. Stir-fry cauliflower, peas, broccoli and carrots in oil 2 minutes. Add zucchini and garlic. Stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in broth. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 2 minutes. Drain fettuccini. Toss with vegetables. Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 2 servings.

title: broccoli and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Drain and cut artichoke hearts into quarters.
Blend butter, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Add to broccoli.
Place artichoke hearts on the bottom of a greased 3-quart casserole.
Add broccoli mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken cheese enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water seasoned with bay leaf, celery and rosemary.
Mix together soups and taco sauce.
Add onion and olives.
Layer tortilla chips, chicken, cheese and soup mix in 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbling in center, about 30 minutes (may want to stir after 15 minutes to even out layers).

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Bake in stem pan at 350° until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut and set aside while creaming margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Then add the milk, coconut and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until golden brown and firm.
(I double this recipe and make 3 pies in shallow pans.)
This makes 1 deep pie.

title: gingerbread bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease lightly with oil and flour an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix oil and water.
Add molasses, sugar and egg whites.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Add to liquid mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until surface springs back when touched lightly.

title: grinder oven sandwich
directions: Add all ingredients except cheese and simmer one hour.
Cut the tops off 2 loaves of French bread.
Hollow out the loaves.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Top with slices of pepper jack cheese.
Replace top of bread and wrap in foil.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10-15 minutes in a 350 degree oven..
Remove from oven and slice. Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream cheese; add marshmallow cream.
When mixed well, add Cool Whip.
Good with fresh fruits, melon balls, etc.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Any combination of fruit you desire can be used.
Example: Mix 1 can crushed pineapple (drained) with 2 thin-sliced bananas. Top with sliced strawberries.

title: la choy chocolate noodle peanut candy
directions: Melt chips over hot water.
Mix noodles and peanuts in a large bowl.
Add chip mixture, mixing well to cover all the noodles. Drop by tablespoonfuls on waxed paper lined cookie sheets and chill until set.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; add sugar.
Stir and add evaporated milk.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: bacon and cheddar chicken
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble bacon. Discard all but 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Dip chicken first in egg, then in breadcrumbs to coat completely.
Saute in hot bacon drippings 4 to 5 minutes over medium-high heat until golden brown on both sides.
When nearly done, top with cheese.
Cover about 30 seconds to melt cheese.
Serve with crumbled bacon.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal yeast bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine milk, butter, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm. Stir in dissolved yeast and eggs.
At medium speed of mixer, beat in 2 cups flour and cornmeal, for 2 minutes.
Gradually add enough remaining flour until dough is soft and leaves the sides of the bowl.
On floured surface, knead dough until smooth and satiny, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in buttered bowl; brush with melted oleo.
Cover and allow to stand in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide in half.

title: never fail doughnuts
directions: Break 3 eggs into mixing bowl and beat- Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat again.
Add 1 cup white syrup and beat again.
Mix well- set to chill- roll and fry in hot fat turning once.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet or Dutch oven.
Saute mushrooms and onion, seasoning with bouillon or soup mix until cooked.
Add hamburger and cook, stirring well to break up lumps, until meat is cooked.
Add tomatoes and macaroni.
Cook, simmering, for 20 minutes until pasta is cooked.
Add cheese, stirring until melted. If mixture is too thin, add tomato soup.

title: zesty zwolle eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mix with sausage, dressing and picante sauce.
Spoon mixture back into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika and top with chopped green onions.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Drain pimientos; reserve juice.
Chop pimientos.
Place potatoes, onion, eggs, pickles and pimientos in salad bowl.
Combine reserved juice and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over potatoes and toss to coat evenly.
Chill for several hours.

title: asian chicken with red onion salsa
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in shallow glass dish.
Add chicken; turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Mix red onions, tomato, green onion, lemon juice, cilantro, balsamic vinegar, olive oil, red pepper and garlic in a glass bowl.
Red pepper can be adjusted for the brave-hearted!
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade; reserve marinade.
Cover and grill chicken 4 to 6 inches from medium coals 15 to 20 minutes, brushing with marinade and turning occasionally until juice is no longer pink. Serve with salsa.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Recipe doubles for Bundt pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm water.
Stir and add oil, buttermilk and flour.
Refrigerate.
Take out what you want and cook.
Do not let it rise first.

title: low-cal baked apples
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam. Layer apple slices. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Add water and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Bring to a boil the first 7 ingredients and sugar if desired. Cool and remove bay leaves.
Add onions, mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Combine all; add shrimp.
Marinate for 24 hours, longer is better, turning or stirring several times.

title: cheesecake the "thick way"
directions: Crust:
Combine 3 tablespoons sugar, crumbs and margarine. Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites till stiff.
Add baking powder, salt, sugar, and vanilla.
Then add nuts and crackers.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes in greased pan.
Cover with whipped cream and place in refrig. until served.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion and celery until tender. Blend in flour; gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and then stir in rice, carrots, almonds, chicken and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in half & half and wine. Heat to serving temperature and add cheese and parsley.

title: yeast bread
directions: Boil the milk and let it cool. Add sugar, shortening, eggs and salt. Mix yeast in warm water and let cool. Then mix with the rest and add flour. Knead. Put in a greased bowl and cover. Let set for 1 1/2 hours and then knead again. Shape in rolls or loaves. Put in greased pan and let rise for 1/2 hour. Bake in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika, and mix thoroughly.
Spread waxed paper heavily with paprika; roll cheese into ball.
It will be soft.
Cover with paprika; wrap in waxed paper.
Place ball in refrigerator until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and salt to soft ball stage, stirring occasionally.
Put pan in cold water and beat in peanut butter. Beat until stiff.
Drop on wax paper or turn onto buttered plate and cut into pieces.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Put melted oleo in a large bowl and toss pecans until all are covered.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper, then stir again.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions which have been thinly sliced (3 cups) in butter until slightly brown (about 15 minutes).
Add beef broth, water and Worcestershire sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.
Put into bowls.
Put one piece toasted French bread on top and cover with cheese.
Broil until slightly brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature. Mix well with hands as mixture is dry.
Shape into 1 inch balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes at 370°.

title: easy cookie bars
directions: Mix oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well. Mix flour and baking powder;
add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Add 1 cup of your choice ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the milk and eggs.
Combine the baking powder to the flour, then to the creamy mixture.
Add extra flour (1 cup).
Roll out dough to about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out with doughnut cutter and fry in hot oil.
Can be rolled in sugar while warm.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Bake chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Cook rice as directed. Fry tortilla shells in hot grease until slightly crisp. (30 seconds on each side) Cut tortilla shells into bite size pieces and dice onion. Add all other ingredients; mix well. Warm in oven in lg. casserole dish or lg. crockpot. Serve!

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan. Stir in soups; add rice and mix well. Arrange chicken on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered, until done.

title: sweet and spicy popcorn
directions: Place dry ingredients in large Ziploc bag or other 2-quart container with lid.
Mix.
Add popped corn.
Spray corn with cooking spray.
Close container and shake.
Repeat spraying and shaking one or two times until well coated.

title: fruit cake
directions: Dredge fruit in one cup of flour; set aside.
Cream oleo and sugar and add to beaten eggs.
Slowly add flour and mix well.
Add prunes, pecans, almonds, raisins, chopped dates and fruit.
Stir well and add mace.
Oil and line pans with wax paper.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
For cupcakes, bake 50 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Top with cheese.
Add remaining mixture.
Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes, or until done.

title: sab burgers
directions: Mix well and shape into patties.
Put on grill or freeze.

title: layered picnic club sandwich
directions: Cut bread in half horizontally; hollow out center of each half, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Spread 1/3 cup creamy Italian dressing into each shell; line bottom shell with lettuce.
In bottom shell layer cheese, roast beef, remaining dressing, turkey then tomato. Top with lettuce; replace top shell.
To serve, cut into wedges.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: creamy vegetable mixturefort morgan, colorado
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, milk and veggies on medium heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat about 15 minutes.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter, peanut butter and vanilla over low heat, stirring constantly.
Empty cereal into a large bowl and pour chocolate mixture over, stirring carefully so you don't break the cereal (or mix with your hands).

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Pour on top of cookie mixture.
Crush a few more cookies and sprinkle on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Can be made in 2 pie tins rather than 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: eggplant moussaka casserole(serves 8)
directions: Heat some oil in a heavy skillet, then add onion and cook until soft and transparent; blend in chopped meat.
Cover and simmer a few minutes.
Stirring constantly, add the wine, tomatoes and herbs, then season with salt and pepper; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Add egg whites and 2 tablespoons of the bread crumbs and blend with a spoon.
Partially peel eggplants by cutting 1/2-inch strips of skin off lengthwise; cut off green stem end, then cut in circles or lengthwise into 1/3-inch slices.
Fry lightly on both sides (or I prefer to brush lightly with oil and bake in a hot oven until slightly golden on both sides.)
Prepare the cream sauce (recipe follows); cool, then add egg yolks and about half the grated cheese and stir well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form a ball.
Roll ball in pecans or walnuts.

title: sweet potato yeast rolls
directions: Heat just warm the milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Add cooled sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle yeast over slowly and combine. Stir in beaten eggs.
Add flour.
Place in greased bowl and let rise in warm place (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Knead lightly and form balls.
Let rise on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with butter.
Cover with wax paper until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush top with a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 cup warm water.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients into ice cream maker and blend for 45 minutes or until ice cream hardens.

title: easy artichoke hearts
directions: Chop artichoke hearts coarsely.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and artichokes.
Pam spray casserole dish.
Put mixture in dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes uncovered until heated through.
Great with Triscuits crackers.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Let cool. Prick holes in tops of brownies with fork and pour liqueur over top; set aside.

title: beanie weanies
directions: Preheat oven to 325° or use medium size pot on top of stove. Combine beans, ketchup and sugar; stir well.
Chop hot dogs into small pieces and add to beans.
Stir occasionally.

title: special k candy
directions: Mix sugar and Karo.
Cook until it boils.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and Special K cereal.
Stir.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Spread in Pyrex dish lined with waxed paper.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes or coarse crumbs.
Combine bread cubes, melted butter, shrimp, salt and pepper and cheese.
Beat eggs slightly and combine with milk.
Pour over shrimp.
Mix and stir well.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Set in a pan of water and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until firm.
Serve with parsley buttered potatoes and green peas.

title: garden patch corn
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomato and parsley.
Cover; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisply tender (10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomato and parsley. Cover; let stand 1 minute or until tomato is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 4-layer pie
directions: Crust:
Mix melted butter, flour and pecans.
Blend together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: czech toast dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and make well in center.

title: fruit glaze
directions: Combine ingredients and fold together.
Chill overnight or 2 hours.

title: greek green beans
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, green beans, garlic, salt and oregano.
Cover; lower heat and simmer 15 minutes or until beans are tender.
Can be served either hot or at room temperature.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: To cold water, add Bisquick and cheese, blending in a mixing bowl. Mix until dough is firm. Using small scoop, place the dough on a baking pan lined with baking paper. Bake at 375 for 10 - 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: indian corn
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large skillet; drain and add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour over low heat.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until creamy. Add eggs, then flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup chips.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle remaining chips over top of bars.
Let stand 5 minutes and spread chocolate over top.

title: make-ahead potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven or large kettle; cover with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain and place in a bowl; mash to desired texture.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, 4 tablespoons of margarine, onion flakes and salt; stir until smooth and the cream cheese and margarine are melted.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt remaining margarine; drizzle over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes; uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
If potatoes are made ahead and refrigerated, let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before baking.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: che-cha
directions: Blanch tomatoes 10 seconds.
Then peel and chop.
Mix tomatoes, basil, garlic and cheese with oil.
Let stand in covered bowl at room temperature for at least 3 hours (the longer the better).
Cook the fusilli according to package directions. Drain.
Add tomato mixture to the pasta.
Mix well.
Serve warm. Serves 5.

title: chow chow
directions: Put vegetables in enamel pot.
Salt and let set overnight or for a few hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and zucchini in butter; add seasoning. Unroll crescent rolls in casserole pan.
Put zucchini on top, then top with Mozzarella.
Scramble 2 eggs and pour on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tennis-golf stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in covered casserole and cook for 5 hours at 250°.
You may add your favorite vegetables, mushrooms, etc., if desired.
Let it bake while you play!

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine. Put with graham crackers as your pie crust. Beat 2 sticks butter with powdered sugar and 1 egg. Beat 15 minutes. Spread over crust. Slice bananas and put over this. Spread pineapple. Top with nuts. Put red cherries on top of this to make it look pretty.

title: ginger cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the sugar, margarine, molasses and egg until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Beat together eggs, salt, pepper and parsley using wire whisk. Add onion, garlic, oil, Parmesan cheese and Bisquick.
Slice and cut into wedges a lot of zucchini.
Stir into mixture.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (top will be golden brown).

title: ruby fruit punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add cranberry juice, lemon and orange juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, turn into punch bowl. Add ginger ale and fruit slices.
Garnish with mint.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: applesauce nut cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add flour alternately with applesauce, mixing well.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: twice-baked potatoes(potato boat)
directions: Cut baked potatoes into halves lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp with teaspoon, keeping potato skin intact.
Place pulp in bowl.
Add salt and margarine; beat until smooth.
Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add green onion and bacon; mix well.
Stir in potato pulp mixture.
Spoon into potato skin.
Sprinkle with cheese and you can add sour cream. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
This can be prepared and frozen, then baked at any time for a quick meal.
